WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:35.100
As-salamu alaykum wa rahmatu Allahi wa barakatuhu

00:00:35.100 --> 00:00:42.800
Bismillahi r-Rahmani r-Rahim, alhamdulillahi rabbil-alameen, wa s-salatu wa s-salamu ala al-mar'uthi rahmatan lil-alameen,

00:00:42.800 --> 00:00:49.700
nabi'ina Muhammadin wa ala alihi wa sahbihi wa t-tabi'ina wa man tabi'ahum bi ihsanin ila yawm al-deen wa ba'a.

00:00:49.700 --> 00:00:55.400
We praise Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala, we send complete blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:00:55.400 --> 00:00:59.000
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless him and his entire household,

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:02.800
and may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless all his companions,

00:01:02.900 --> 00:01:07.200
and may he bless every single one of us and grant us goodness and ease.

00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:14.000
Beloved brothers and sisters, we thank Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala for giving us this opportunity to gather in one of his houses,

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:20.300
for indeed with the cold spell that we are facing in this part of the world, masha'Allah,

00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:25.400
and the snow that we've heard of in most of the country or parts of the country today,

00:01:25.400 --> 00:01:33.100
wallahi, for every moment that we bear this, it is indeed a means of elevation of our status,

00:01:33.100 --> 00:01:35.300
and by the will of Allah, we should be grateful,

00:01:35.300 --> 00:01:39.900
there are others in other parts of the world who have extremely long fasts,

00:01:39.900 --> 00:01:45.200
and at the same time, they have the heat of summer on top of it, may Allah make it easy for them as well,

00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:50.200
and we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to grant us all acceptance every single category,

00:01:50.200 --> 00:01:53.800
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:57.700
The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم and the battle of Uhud,

00:01:57.700 --> 00:02:08.100
we had made mention of how the battle took a turn when the Muslims were sandwiched between the little platoon of Khalid ibn al-Walid رضي الله عنه.

00:02:08.100 --> 00:02:12.200
At that time, he was not yet a Muslim, he was part of the Mushrik army,

00:02:12.200 --> 00:02:17.700
and the army of Makkah on the other side, and they suffered great losses,

00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:21.200
and we had made mention of that in quite a bit of detail yesterday.

00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:25.900
A point that came to my mind which I felt would have been of interest was,

00:02:25.900 --> 00:02:29.500
as I had said previously regarding the battle of Badr,

00:02:29.500 --> 00:02:36.200
every war, the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم vetted the people who took part in the war one by one,

00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:39.700
and he studied their cases, most of them he would have known them,

00:02:39.700 --> 00:02:42.200
so it wouldn't require more than a split second,

00:02:42.200 --> 00:02:48.700
but some of the cases he would ask them questions and thereafter send them back or allow them to join the army.

00:02:48.700 --> 00:02:53.800
From amongst them were two youngsters, they wanted to take part in the battle of Uhud,

00:02:53.800 --> 00:02:59.000
Samurah ibn, in fact, Rafi' ibn Khadij and Samurah ibn Jundub رضي الله عنهما,

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:02.900
two young people in their teenage at the time,

00:03:02.900 --> 00:03:06.300
and the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم was sending both of them back,

00:03:06.300 --> 00:03:11.500
but he was told that Rafi' ibn Khadij رضي الله عنه was very good at his arrows,

00:03:11.500 --> 00:03:16.300
he could aim very well, and he was really really good in his aiming,

00:03:16.300 --> 00:03:19.600
so the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم decided to take him with,

00:03:19.600 --> 00:03:23.000
and at this point Samurah ibn Jundub رضي الله عنه,

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:26.400
who saw that his friend was going and he was being chased back,

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:32.300
he began to cry, and he says to his stepfather that you know this person,

00:03:32.300 --> 00:03:36.000
meaning this person, the other companion is gone,

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:39.000
and yet if the two of us had to fight now,

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:43.600
I would out wrestle him, if we had to wrestle I would put him on the ground in a minute,

00:03:43.600 --> 00:03:47.500
so when this news got to Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم he called him back,

00:03:47.500 --> 00:03:50.900
he says okay here's the two of you, let's see who can wrestle who,

00:03:50.900 --> 00:03:56.100
and do you know what, Subhanallah, Samurah ibn Jundub in no time put Rafi' ibn Khadij on the floor,

00:03:56.100 --> 00:04:01.400
Subhanallah, and so the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم allowed them both to take part in this battle of Uhud,

00:04:01.400 --> 00:04:03.900
Subhanallah, look at how beautiful it was,

00:04:03.900 --> 00:04:06.600
in front of him he told him you can wrestle the two of you,

00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:10.400
whoever out wrestles, or if you out wrestle him you will come as it is,

00:04:10.400 --> 00:04:13.400
he was already written from amongst those who was meant to go,

00:04:13.400 --> 00:04:15.800
so that was a very interesting story,

00:04:15.800 --> 00:04:21.400
thereafter the battle took place and as we know when the Muslims were sandwiched,

00:04:21.400 --> 00:04:23.100
they suffered great losses,

00:04:23.100 --> 00:04:29.700
and at the same time the Kuffar of Quraysh were shocked at the courage of the Muslims,

00:04:29.700 --> 00:04:33.500
they were some of the heroes of the battle of Uhud,

00:04:33.500 --> 00:04:37.000
and some of these heroes we have to make mention of Sayyid al-Shuhada,

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:40.800
who was Hamzah ibn Abdul Muttalib رضي الله عنه,

00:04:40.900 --> 00:04:45.800
although he had not been alive to witness the end of that battle,

00:04:45.800 --> 00:04:49.300
but he was one of the first who was actually martyred,

00:04:49.300 --> 00:04:54.100
and the killer or the one who killed him was known as Wahshi,

00:04:54.100 --> 00:04:56.400
this Wahshi we will speak about him in a few minutes,

00:04:56.400 --> 00:05:01.700
but the others who were heroes Talhah ibn Ubaydi Allah رضي الله عنه,

00:05:01.700 --> 00:05:04.600
he personally stood around Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم,

00:05:04.600 --> 00:05:10.500
and took so many spears and arrows in order to defend Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم,

00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:14.500
and this is why in one narration the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم says,

00:05:14.500 --> 00:05:17.000
if we were to say whose day this was,

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:20.600
we could comfortably say this was the day of Talhah ibn Ubaydi Allah رضي الله عنه,

00:05:20.600 --> 00:05:27.000
may Allah سبحانه وتعالى grant him Jannah رضي الله عنه وعن الجميع,

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:31.500
the other heroes of this particular war Mus'ab ibn Umayr رضي الله عنه,

00:05:31.500 --> 00:05:34.500
we spoke about him yesterday in a little bit of detail,

00:05:34.500 --> 00:05:37.800
and we made mention of how he held the flag up with one hand,

00:05:37.800 --> 00:05:43.900
when they had cut his hand off, he then held it with the other hand,

00:05:43.900 --> 00:05:46.600
and thereafter when they had slipped the other hand,

00:05:46.600 --> 00:05:50.000
he then held it close to his chest with the remainder of his hand,

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.700
may Allah سبحانه وتعالى grant us goodness,

00:05:52.700 --> 00:05:55.400
he was on that day also martyred,

00:05:55.400 --> 00:05:59.100
another one was Sahel ibn Hunayf and Abu Dujana,

00:05:59.100 --> 00:06:05.300
Sahel ibn Hunayf was also a warrior who had really engaged in much on that particular day,

00:06:05.300 --> 00:06:07.300
and then he lost his life, he was martyred,

00:06:07.300 --> 00:06:10.400
and as for Abu Dujana, he was a warrior of note,

00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:14.200
he was a man who used to wear a red little rope on his head,

00:06:14.200 --> 00:06:18.900
he had a red band on his head that he used to wear when he was very very upset,

00:06:18.900 --> 00:06:21.700
and when he was serious in war,

00:06:21.700 --> 00:06:23.500
and so this Abu Dujana,

00:06:23.500 --> 00:06:26.700
the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم lifted his own sword and said,

00:06:26.700 --> 00:06:30.400
who will take this sword with its right?

00:06:30.400 --> 00:06:34.200
and the people wanted it, some of the Sahabah رضي الله عنهم wanted it,

00:06:34.200 --> 00:06:37.700
he did not give anyone, but when Abu Dujana requested it,

00:06:37.700 --> 00:06:40.000
he was granted that particular sword,

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:42.100
and he asked what is its right?

00:06:42.100 --> 00:06:44.600
So the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم informed him

00:06:44.600 --> 00:06:47.300
that you should make use of it right to the end,

00:06:47.300 --> 00:06:49.000
and very very true,

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:52.100
this man was seen not only by Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم,

00:06:52.100 --> 00:06:55.100
but even by the other companions on that particular day,

00:06:55.100 --> 00:06:56.900
up and down, Subhanallah,

00:06:56.900 --> 00:07:00.500
and he really defended Islam and the Muslims in a very big way

00:07:00.500 --> 00:07:02.300
until he himself was martyred.

00:07:02.300 --> 00:07:06.300
Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم says the way he is walking,

00:07:06.300 --> 00:07:10.800
the way he is walking through the lines of the enemy,

00:07:10.800 --> 00:07:13.400
you know that haughtiness that he is walking with,

00:07:13.400 --> 00:07:16.500
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala does not like that haughtiness

00:07:16.500 --> 00:07:19.500
except in this particular instance,

00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:21.000
in the instance of war,

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.500
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:07:23.500 --> 00:07:26.600
and may he make us from those who understand.

00:07:26.600 --> 00:07:31.500
Also the angels took part in this particular battle as well,

00:07:31.500 --> 00:07:35.800
and remember there is a hadith of Sa'd ibn Abi Waqqas

00:07:35.800 --> 00:07:37.500
reported in Sahih al-Bukhari,

00:07:37.500 --> 00:07:41.700
where he says that I remember seeing people in white

00:07:41.700 --> 00:07:44.700
whom I had not known taking part in this battle,

00:07:44.700 --> 00:07:46.400
later the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم says

00:07:46.400 --> 00:07:48.100
that was Jibreel and Mika'il,

00:07:48.100 --> 00:07:50.700
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us protection.

00:07:50.700 --> 00:07:55.700
One might ask why was there no decisive victory for the Muslims

00:07:55.700 --> 00:07:58.200
if the angels were also there?

00:07:58.200 --> 00:08:00.100
Very simple answer,

00:08:00.100 --> 00:08:03.500
because they did not follow instructions,

00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:05.800
they did not obey the messenger,

00:08:05.800 --> 00:08:08.200
they disobeyed the instruction of the messenger

00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:09.900
صلى الله عليه وسلم.

00:08:09.900 --> 00:08:12.300
And in our lives, let's remember one thing,

00:08:12.300 --> 00:08:14.800
wherever we have disobeyed Allah

00:08:14.800 --> 00:08:17.300
and wherever we have disobeyed the Rasul of Allah

00:08:17.300 --> 00:08:19.200
subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:22.800
we will then be suffering some form of a loss

00:08:22.800 --> 00:08:25.400
either in the near future or later on

00:08:25.400 --> 00:08:27.900
unless we repent before it comes to us.

00:08:27.900 --> 00:08:30.000
Allah does us a favor,

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:34.400
in a lot of instances we are given some reprieve, some time.

00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:36.000
You know a person is transgressing,

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:37.700
they go against the commands of Allah,

00:08:37.700 --> 00:08:39.300
Allah gives them some time

00:08:39.300 --> 00:08:41.900
and after they are given perhaps sometimes a few days,

00:08:41.900 --> 00:08:44.500
sometimes a few years, sometimes a longer time

00:08:44.500 --> 00:08:46.900
and the person continues transgressing,

00:08:46.900 --> 00:08:48.700
one day when the rope is pulled,

00:08:48.700 --> 00:08:50.900
it is pulled completely.

00:08:50.900 --> 00:08:53.000
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala not do that to us

00:08:53.000 --> 00:08:54.500
and may He not punish us.

00:08:54.500 --> 00:08:57.700
But if we have repented before the punishment comes,

00:08:57.700 --> 00:09:01.100
perhaps it will be diverted by the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:09:01.100 --> 00:09:07.300
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala wanted something to happen on that day

00:09:07.300 --> 00:09:09.300
and that was a lesson for them.

00:09:09.300 --> 00:09:11.500
There was no other battle after this

00:09:11.500 --> 00:09:15.000
where they had suffered this type of humiliation.

00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:16.600
Always after this,

00:09:16.600 --> 00:09:18.000
there was some form of victory

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:20.800
or Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala had opened their doors

00:09:20.800 --> 00:09:23.700
even without a battle in some cases.

00:09:23.700 --> 00:09:25.300
But in this particular case,

00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:28.600
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala wanted to strengthen them,

00:09:28.600 --> 00:09:31.100
to say you should obey instruction

00:09:31.100 --> 00:09:34.600
and it is only through the obedience of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:09:34.600 --> 00:09:36.900
that you will achieve success in this dunya,

00:09:36.900 --> 00:09:39.400
in this world as well as in the life after death.

00:09:39.400 --> 00:09:42.300
The Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam cried

00:09:42.300 --> 00:09:44.100
when he saw his uncle Hamzah,

00:09:44.100 --> 00:09:46.000
Ibn Abdul Muttalib.

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:48.800
What they had done was mutilated the bodies

00:09:48.800 --> 00:09:52.300
of a lot of those who were martyred on that day.

00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:53.200
And astaghfirullah,

00:09:53.200 --> 00:09:54.800
they brought with them their women

00:09:54.800 --> 00:09:56.200
in order to do that.

00:09:56.200 --> 00:09:58.500
So Hamzah Ibn Abdul Muttalib,

00:09:58.500 --> 00:09:59.700
Sayyid al-Shuhada,

00:09:59.700 --> 00:10:01.200
the leader of the martyrs,

00:10:01.200 --> 00:10:05.600
he was mutilated by a woman

00:10:05.600 --> 00:10:07.900
known as Hind binti Utbah.

00:10:07.900 --> 00:10:10.000
Because Utbah was one of those

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:12.500
who was killed by Hamzah in the Battle of Badr,

00:10:12.500 --> 00:10:15.800
this woman was not at all comfortable

00:10:15.800 --> 00:10:18.500
until she slit his belly.

00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:20.700
Allahu Akbar, Allah safeguard us,

00:10:20.700 --> 00:10:23.100
removed his liver and actually chewed on it.

00:10:23.100 --> 00:10:24.700
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:10:24.700 --> 00:10:27.300
protect us from this type of gruesome behavior

00:10:27.300 --> 00:10:29.000
and may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:30.800
grant us an understanding.

00:10:30.800 --> 00:10:33.400
The Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam said very clearly,

00:10:33.400 --> 00:10:35.300
Muslims do not mutilate.

00:10:35.300 --> 00:10:38.300
You neither mutilate your body whilst you're alive.

00:10:38.300 --> 00:10:40.300
And this is why permanent tattooing

00:10:40.300 --> 00:10:42.600
and so on is all prohibited in Islam.

00:10:42.600 --> 00:10:44.500
To pierce yourself in different places

00:10:44.500 --> 00:10:46.700
besides the ears and perhaps the nose,

00:10:46.700 --> 00:10:49.000
after that is not permissible in the Sharia.

00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:50.400
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:10:50.400 --> 00:10:53.000
protect us from mutilating our own bodies.

00:10:53.000 --> 00:10:54.800
And may He make us understand

00:10:54.800 --> 00:10:56.800
what is mutilation in the first place.

00:10:56.800 --> 00:10:58.300
Because many people don't know.

00:10:58.300 --> 00:11:02.900
This body is entrusted to us by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:11:02.900 --> 00:11:04.200
He's going to take it back

00:11:04.200 --> 00:11:05.500
and He's going to ask us

00:11:05.500 --> 00:11:07.900
how did we look after it and protect it?

00:11:07.900 --> 00:11:08.600
How can we say,

00:11:08.600 --> 00:11:11.100
okay, I made a hole here and a hole there and a hole there

00:11:11.100 --> 00:11:13.300
and this may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:11:13.300 --> 00:11:14.800
protect us and safeguard us.

00:11:14.800 --> 00:11:17.000
We've only spoken about something very light.

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:19.800
But believe me, the Sharia has deep laws

00:11:19.800 --> 00:11:21.600
which would actually result

00:11:21.700 --> 00:11:24.400
if we followed them in our success in this world

00:11:24.400 --> 00:11:25.300
as well as in the next.

00:11:25.300 --> 00:11:27.200
May Allah make it easy for us.

00:11:27.200 --> 00:11:30.600
And this is why Safiyah binti Abdul Muttalib,

00:11:30.600 --> 00:11:33.300
the sister of Hamza radiallahu anhu,

00:11:33.300 --> 00:11:37.300
she wanted to see the body of her own brother.

00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:39.000
Now there was a rule that was passed

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:41.100
by Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:11:41.100 --> 00:11:42.600
Don't let the women come

00:11:42.600 --> 00:11:45.100
and see the bodies of their own relatives.

00:11:45.100 --> 00:11:47.600
Why? Because those who are mutilated,

00:11:47.600 --> 00:11:51.300
they may go back with a very different image of this person.

00:11:51.300 --> 00:11:54.700
It is best that they go with the image they recall.

00:11:54.700 --> 00:11:56.800
And this is why the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:11:56.800 --> 00:11:58.800
told them take Safiyah back

00:11:58.800 --> 00:12:01.900
and do not let her look at her brother.

00:12:01.900 --> 00:12:04.200
It may hurt her heart emotionally and so on.

00:12:04.200 --> 00:12:05.800
And the picture that remains,

00:12:05.800 --> 00:12:07.700
the image that remains in the mind

00:12:07.700 --> 00:12:11.300
will always be that of someone totally mutilated.

00:12:11.300 --> 00:12:13.400
But Safiyah was one exception.

00:12:13.400 --> 00:12:15.900
She spoke to the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:12:15.900 --> 00:12:18.300
and said, oh messenger, I will bear patience.

00:12:18.300 --> 00:12:19.400
I will make dua.

00:12:19.500 --> 00:12:21.300
I will not be emotional

00:12:21.300 --> 00:12:23.800
and start screaming and yelling and so on,

00:12:23.800 --> 00:12:25.400
but I need to see my brother.

00:12:25.400 --> 00:12:27.400
And so for her, permission was granted.

00:12:27.400 --> 00:12:29.400
But we learned a lesson

00:12:29.400 --> 00:12:31.000
that sometimes when a death happens

00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:35.500
and it is not so good to the eye,

00:12:35.500 --> 00:12:38.100
it is definitely an Islamic ruling

00:12:38.100 --> 00:12:40.400
to stop some of the family members

00:12:40.400 --> 00:12:42.700
from looking at that particular face

00:12:42.700 --> 00:12:46.000
if perhaps it is heavily injured or mutilated

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:48.400
and sometimes perhaps in a few pieces,

00:12:48.400 --> 00:12:50.500
say after a car crash or so on,

00:12:50.500 --> 00:12:51.700
may Allah protect us.

00:12:51.700 --> 00:12:53.700
Sometimes you have instances

00:12:53.700 --> 00:12:55.600
where the faces or the head

00:12:55.600 --> 00:12:58.000
is actually broken into pieces.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:12:59.400
May Allah safeguard us.

00:12:59.400 --> 00:13:02.300
It is not wrong for the ulama to get up

00:13:02.300 --> 00:13:03.500
and family members to say,

00:13:03.500 --> 00:13:04.600
look, the women folk,

00:13:04.600 --> 00:13:05.600
you will not be allowed

00:13:05.600 --> 00:13:08.400
to view the face of this particular person.

00:13:08.400 --> 00:13:10.800
This is from the teaching of Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:13:10.800 --> 00:13:13.900
It is best for them to have the last good image

00:13:13.900 --> 00:13:15.300
within their minds

00:13:15.300 --> 00:13:16.300
than to have an image

00:13:16.300 --> 00:13:18.000
which will remain forever and ever.

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:19.400
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:13:19.400 --> 00:13:21.500
protect us all and grant us goodness.

00:13:21.500 --> 00:13:24.100
As for Wahshi, that man,

00:13:24.100 --> 00:13:27.900
he reports that when I killed Hamza radiallahu anhu,

00:13:27.900 --> 00:13:29.900
immediately something struck me.

00:13:29.900 --> 00:13:32.100
I knew I was going to be a free man

00:13:32.100 --> 00:13:34.300
as per the promise of Jubair ibn Mut'im

00:13:34.300 --> 00:13:36.100
who was my master.

00:13:36.100 --> 00:13:37.200
And at the same time,

00:13:37.200 --> 00:13:39.800
I felt enslaved by something else.

00:13:39.800 --> 00:13:43.200
I felt captured by something far greater

00:13:43.200 --> 00:13:45.700
than the enslaving that I was in.

00:13:45.700 --> 00:13:47.700
And he says to the degree

00:13:47.800 --> 00:13:48.900
that when I was free,

00:13:48.900 --> 00:13:50.300
I was back in Makkah,

00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:51.500
but I couldn't do anything.

00:13:51.500 --> 00:13:53.400
I could not sleep in the night.

00:13:53.400 --> 00:13:55.600
I constantly thought of this deed

00:13:55.600 --> 00:13:57.100
that I had engaged in

00:13:57.100 --> 00:13:59.000
and I became a drunkard.

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:01.300
He says I became a drunkard so much so

00:14:01.300 --> 00:14:03.400
that I was neither fit for living

00:14:03.400 --> 00:14:04.600
nor for the dead.

00:14:04.600 --> 00:14:05.800
And there came a degree,

00:14:05.800 --> 00:14:08.000
a time when the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:09.600
marched on to Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:14:09.600 --> 00:14:10.600
with his army.

00:14:10.600 --> 00:14:12.100
He says I was too embarrassed.

00:14:12.100 --> 00:14:14.200
I left and I went to Ta'if

00:14:14.200 --> 00:14:15.500
and I spent some time there

00:14:15.500 --> 00:14:18.000
until after the victory of Makkah,

00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:19.800
the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam sent for me

00:14:19.800 --> 00:14:24.500
and I came to Makkah al-Mukarramah from Ta'if.

00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:27.500
And he says when I saw the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:14:27.500 --> 00:14:28.100
he asked me,

00:14:28.100 --> 00:14:30.200
are you Wahshi?

00:14:30.200 --> 00:14:33.100
Are you the killer of my uncle Hamza?

00:14:33.100 --> 00:14:34.100
And Hamza was the uncle

00:14:34.100 --> 00:14:34.900
and at the same time,

00:14:34.900 --> 00:14:38.400
he was a foster brother of Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:14:38.400 --> 00:14:39.800
So he says yes.

00:14:39.800 --> 00:14:42.800
So although Wahshi became a Muslim,

00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:44.000
the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:14:44.100 --> 00:14:46.300
made one request to him.

00:14:46.300 --> 00:14:47.700
He says look,

00:14:47.700 --> 00:14:50.800
if you can stay away from me as far as possible,

00:14:50.800 --> 00:14:52.100
every time I see you,

00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:53.400
I remember my uncle.

00:14:53.400 --> 00:14:54.900
Subhanallah.

00:14:54.900 --> 00:14:57.200
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:14:57.200 --> 00:14:58.700
This was one thing

00:14:58.700 --> 00:14:59.800
and this is why Wahshi,

00:14:59.800 --> 00:15:01.200
he says I lived

00:15:01.200 --> 00:15:04.300
and I was so indebted to what had happened

00:15:04.300 --> 00:15:06.100
because I felt so bad

00:15:06.100 --> 00:15:08.800
until after Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:10.100
I heard of Musaylamah,

00:15:10.100 --> 00:15:11.100
Al-Kadhaab,

00:15:11.100 --> 00:15:13.800
the liar who claimed prophethood, Musaylamah.

00:15:13.800 --> 00:15:15.600
He says and I made a dua to Allah,

00:15:15.600 --> 00:15:17.000
Ya Allah, I'm joining the army

00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:19.800
who is going to see this man and attack him

00:15:19.800 --> 00:15:22.500
and Allah make me from amongst those

00:15:22.500 --> 00:15:24.300
who can execute that liar

00:15:24.300 --> 00:15:26.700
and indeed Allah granted him that

00:15:26.700 --> 00:15:29.000
and this is when he felt a little bit at ease

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:31.600
when he was used to execute Musaylamah,

00:15:31.600 --> 00:15:32.600
Al-Kadhaab,

00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:35.200
the liar who had claimed prophethood

00:15:35.200 --> 00:15:38.900
when the Muslims had gone there to attack him with his army.

00:15:38.900 --> 00:15:40.900
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us protection.

00:15:40.900 --> 00:15:42.900
So this was Wahshi.

00:15:42.900 --> 00:15:45.200
Then comes the burial of those

00:15:45.200 --> 00:15:47.300
who had died in the battle of Uhud.

00:15:47.300 --> 00:15:49.600
There were approximately 70 Muslims

00:15:49.600 --> 00:15:52.000
who had been martyred in the battle of Uhud.

00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:54.800
Most of them were from the Ansar.

00:15:54.800 --> 00:15:56.400
And the Prophet salallahu alayhi wasallam

00:15:56.400 --> 00:15:59.400
asked who has memorized more Quran.

00:15:59.400 --> 00:16:01.000
The one who memorized more Quran

00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:02.800
was put into the grave first

00:16:02.800 --> 00:16:04.800
and each grave had more than one person,

00:16:04.800 --> 00:16:06.400
some of them two, some of them three,

00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:08.300
depending on what was available

00:16:08.300 --> 00:16:10.800
because they could not dig so many graves

00:16:10.800 --> 00:16:12.800
and this is why in the Shari'ah,

00:16:12.800 --> 00:16:16.300
the grave that you are buried in,

00:16:16.300 --> 00:16:19.100
we in Islam allow

00:16:19.100 --> 00:16:23.100
for burial in the same spot some time later

00:16:23.100 --> 00:16:26.800
because once the body has decomposed into the soil,

00:16:26.800 --> 00:16:30.400
it is now fit for re-burial.

00:16:30.400 --> 00:16:32.400
In our parts of the world this doesn't happen

00:16:32.400 --> 00:16:34.100
because I think in most cases

00:16:34.100 --> 00:16:35.600
you purchase the little piece of land,

00:16:35.600 --> 00:16:36.800
it becomes yours.

00:16:36.800 --> 00:16:38.800
But where the Maqbara

00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:40.600
or where the graveyard is Waqf,

00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:42.100
it is an endowment,

00:16:42.100 --> 00:16:44.400
you find that there is no harm in burying again

00:16:44.400 --> 00:16:45.900
and again in the same place,

00:16:45.900 --> 00:16:48.800
perhaps a year, two years, nine years, ten years later

00:16:48.800 --> 00:16:51.300
as happens even in Baqi',

00:16:51.300 --> 00:16:53.500
the graveyard of Madinatul Munawwara.

00:16:53.500 --> 00:16:55.200
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:57.100
grant us a deep understanding.

00:16:57.100 --> 00:16:58.600
So when they were burying,

00:16:58.600 --> 00:17:00.800
they found a lot of these poor people.

00:17:00.800 --> 00:17:02.300
Some of them were martyrs

00:17:02.300 --> 00:17:04.200
in the path of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:17:04.200 --> 00:17:06.200
after having fought and served Islam

00:17:06.200 --> 00:17:07.300
for a long time,

00:17:07.300 --> 00:17:08.900
such as Mus'ab ibn Romayr,

00:17:08.900 --> 00:17:12.400
when he was brought to be buried,

00:17:12.400 --> 00:17:13.800
there was nothing to cover him.

00:17:13.800 --> 00:17:16.500
The Prophet ﷺ issued an instruction,

00:17:16.500 --> 00:17:18.000
all those who were martyred,

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:19.600
there is no washing for them,

00:17:19.600 --> 00:17:20.700
no ghusl for them.

00:17:20.700 --> 00:17:22.400
They should be buried in their clothing

00:17:22.400 --> 00:17:23.800
with the stains of blood.

00:17:23.800 --> 00:17:26.100
They will be resurrected on the Day of Qiyamah,

00:17:26.100 --> 00:17:27.800
the color will be the color of blood

00:17:27.800 --> 00:17:29.900
and the smell will be the smell of musk.

00:17:29.900 --> 00:17:33.400
This is what Rasulullah ﷺ had said.

00:17:33.400 --> 00:17:34.900
But Mus'ab ibn Umayr,

00:17:34.900 --> 00:17:36.400
when they covered his head,

00:17:36.400 --> 00:17:37.600
his feet showed.

00:17:37.600 --> 00:17:38.700
When they covered his feet,

00:17:38.700 --> 00:17:39.600
his head showed.

00:17:39.600 --> 00:17:41.800
So they did not have enough to cover him.

00:17:41.800 --> 00:17:44.600
And the Prophet ﷺ makes mention of something

00:17:44.600 --> 00:17:45.600
very very interesting.

00:17:45.600 --> 00:17:48.000
He says this was one of the richest

00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:49.800
of the youngsters of Makkah.

00:17:49.800 --> 00:17:52.100
And today there is nothing to cover him.

00:17:52.100 --> 00:17:54.700
And he has passed away in this condition.

00:17:54.700 --> 00:18:04.000
من المؤمنين رجال صدقوا ما عاهدوا الله عليه

00:18:04.000 --> 00:18:08.400
فمنهم من قضا نحبه

00:18:08.400 --> 00:18:13.500
ومنهم من ينتظر

00:18:13.500 --> 00:18:17.800
وما بدلوا تبديلا

00:18:17.800 --> 00:18:19.800
From amongst the believers,

00:18:19.800 --> 00:18:21.800
they are those who have fulfilled

00:18:21.800 --> 00:18:24.600
their promise unto Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:18:24.600 --> 00:18:26.200
Some of them have been martyred

00:18:26.200 --> 00:18:27.800
and the others are in waiting.

00:18:27.800 --> 00:18:29.100
الله أكبر

00:18:29.100 --> 00:18:30.500
Some of them have been martyred

00:18:30.500 --> 00:18:32.100
and the others have been waiting.

00:18:32.100 --> 00:18:33.800
The Prophet ﷺ says

00:18:33.800 --> 00:18:35.800
حمزة ممن قضا نحبه

00:18:35.800 --> 00:18:37.600
مصعب ممن قضا نحبه

00:18:37.600 --> 00:18:38.900
He took names of people.

00:18:38.900 --> 00:18:41.500
These are the people who have been martyred

00:18:41.500 --> 00:18:45.700
fulfilling their promise unto Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:18:45.700 --> 00:18:47.200
So Mus'ab ibn Umayr,

00:18:47.200 --> 00:18:50.200
the Prophet ﷺ says cover his head

00:18:50.200 --> 00:18:51.200
and as for his feet,

00:18:51.200 --> 00:18:53.000
you can use a bit of the idkhir,

00:18:53.100 --> 00:18:55.700
a little bit of a branch

00:18:55.700 --> 00:18:57.700
that you can actually cover it with

00:18:57.700 --> 00:18:59.200
and that is how he was buried.

00:18:59.200 --> 00:19:00.600
One narration in Zahidul Ma'ad

00:19:00.600 --> 00:19:03.000
makes mention of Hamza ibn Abd al-Muttalib

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:04.300
with a similar condition.

00:19:04.300 --> 00:19:05.900
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:19:05.900 --> 00:19:07.200
grant us a deep understanding.

00:19:07.200 --> 00:19:08.000
Remember,

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:10.500
what comes with us in the grave

00:19:10.500 --> 00:19:12.600
is our deeds,

00:19:12.600 --> 00:19:14.100
not our wealth

00:19:14.100 --> 00:19:16.000
and not what we look like

00:19:16.000 --> 00:19:17.800
but what comes into our graves,

00:19:17.800 --> 00:19:18.600
our deeds.

00:19:18.600 --> 00:19:20.500
So let us do the best of deeds

00:19:20.500 --> 00:19:21.800
before it is too late

00:19:21.800 --> 00:19:23.100
and prepare for the day

00:19:23.100 --> 00:19:24.700
when we will pass away

00:19:24.700 --> 00:19:27.000
and meet Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:29.400
On their return,

00:19:29.400 --> 00:19:31.900
Hamnah binti Jahsh,

00:19:31.900 --> 00:19:34.200
radiallahu anha,

00:19:34.200 --> 00:19:37.500
she was told that your brother

00:19:37.500 --> 00:19:39.200
has been martyred.

00:19:39.200 --> 00:19:41.700
Abdullah ibn Jahsh has been martyred.

00:19:41.700 --> 00:19:43.400
So she made a dua for him

00:19:43.400 --> 00:19:45.600
and she said may Allah grant us the patience.

00:19:45.600 --> 00:19:47.600
Then she was told your uncle

00:19:47.600 --> 00:19:49.100
has also been martyred,

00:19:49.100 --> 00:19:51.300
Hamza ibn Abd al-Muttalib.

00:19:51.300 --> 00:19:52.900
She made a dua for him

00:19:52.900 --> 00:19:55.400
and she was patient.

00:19:55.400 --> 00:19:56.300
Then she was told

00:19:56.300 --> 00:19:58.700
and your husband has also been martyred,

00:19:58.700 --> 00:20:00.200
Mus'ab ibn Umair.

00:20:00.200 --> 00:20:02.200
Then she yelled.

00:20:02.200 --> 00:20:03.900
She let out a little bit of a scream.

00:20:03.900 --> 00:20:05.900
Then she also made the dua and so on.

00:20:05.900 --> 00:20:07.500
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:20:07.500 --> 00:20:08.700
immediately said

00:20:08.700 --> 00:20:11.200
the husband is closer to the heart

00:20:11.200 --> 00:20:13.700
than the brothers and the uncles.

00:20:13.700 --> 00:20:14.900
Subhanallah.

00:20:14.900 --> 00:20:16.400
This is the heart of a woman.

00:20:16.400 --> 00:20:18.200
If we are true husbands,

00:20:18.200 --> 00:20:21.100
our wives become closer to us

00:20:21.100 --> 00:20:24.000
than they are to their own family members.

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:26.300
Because we become the new family

00:20:26.300 --> 00:20:28.200
and their children become the new blood.

00:20:28.200 --> 00:20:29.500
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:29.500 --> 00:20:31.300
grant us a deep understanding.

00:20:31.300 --> 00:20:33.000
Look at Mus'ab ibn Umair.

00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:35.000
What a powerful man he was.

00:20:35.000 --> 00:20:36.400
He was such a gentleman,

00:20:36.400 --> 00:20:37.700
such a sahabi,

00:20:37.700 --> 00:20:38.900
radiallahu anhu.

00:20:38.900 --> 00:20:43.000
He was lost or martyred in the battle of Uhud.

00:20:43.000 --> 00:20:44.200
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:44.200 --> 00:20:45.500
grant him Jannah.

00:20:45.500 --> 00:20:46.700
Then there is a woman,

00:20:46.700 --> 00:20:48.000
a famous woman.

00:20:48.000 --> 00:20:49.300
Her name is not mentioned

00:20:49.300 --> 00:20:51.000
but she is a woman from

00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:53.880
Banu Dinah.

00:20:53.880 --> 00:20:55.780
They told her,

00:20:55.780 --> 00:20:56.980
your husband is martyred,

00:20:56.980 --> 00:20:58.180
your brother is martyred

00:20:58.180 --> 00:20:59.480
and your father is martyred.

00:20:59.480 --> 00:21:00.880
All three of them.

00:21:00.880 --> 00:21:01.680
She said,

00:21:01.680 --> 00:21:03.980
what about the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam?

00:21:03.980 --> 00:21:05.080
What did the Prophet do?

00:21:05.080 --> 00:21:07.280
What about the Prophet?

00:21:07.280 --> 00:21:08.280
They said, no, he is fine.

00:21:08.280 --> 00:21:08.780
He is okay.

00:21:08.780 --> 00:21:09.880
She said, no, where is he?

00:21:09.880 --> 00:21:10.880
I would like to look at him.

00:21:10.880 --> 00:21:12.380
I want to see him.

00:21:12.380 --> 00:21:13.980
And then they waited for a moment

00:21:13.980 --> 00:21:15.280
until he came through.

00:21:15.280 --> 00:21:17.080
When she saw him,

00:21:17.080 --> 00:21:18.580
she smiled and said,

00:21:18.580 --> 00:21:21.380
كل مصيبة بعده هينا

00:21:21.380 --> 00:21:24.080
All difficulties after this are easy.

00:21:24.080 --> 00:21:25.280
If he is okay,

00:21:25.280 --> 00:21:26.580
everything else is fine.

00:21:26.580 --> 00:21:27.380
Subhanallah.

00:21:27.380 --> 00:21:28.580
This was the response

00:21:28.580 --> 00:21:30.180
of the Sahabiyat at the time.

00:21:30.180 --> 00:21:31.380
They were more concerned

00:21:31.380 --> 00:21:33.680
about Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:33.680 --> 00:21:35.480
than their own family members.

00:21:35.480 --> 00:21:37.780
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless them

00:21:37.780 --> 00:21:39.180
and may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:21:39.180 --> 00:21:39.980
grant us goodness.

00:21:39.980 --> 00:21:40.780
With us,

00:21:40.780 --> 00:21:43.380
we sometimes become more concerned

00:21:43.380 --> 00:21:45.080
about sinning

00:21:45.080 --> 00:21:46.680
than we are about our link

00:21:46.680 --> 00:21:47.880
with our own maker

00:21:47.880 --> 00:21:50.680
and our link with Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:21:50.680 --> 00:21:52.880
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us.

00:21:52.880 --> 00:21:54.780
This was not an issue of sinning.

00:21:54.780 --> 00:21:55.780
If she had cried

00:21:55.780 --> 00:21:56.880
or if she had wept

00:21:56.880 --> 00:21:58.380
or if something else had happened

00:21:58.380 --> 00:22:00.680
in terms of her tears and so on,

00:22:00.680 --> 00:22:01.980
it wouldn't have been bad.

00:22:01.980 --> 00:22:02.780
She was worried.

00:22:02.780 --> 00:22:04.080
ما فعل رسول الله

00:22:04.080 --> 00:22:04.980
First question.

00:22:04.980 --> 00:22:05.780
Leave all that.

00:22:05.780 --> 00:22:08.880
Tell me about the Messenger sallallahu alayhi wasallam.

00:22:08.880 --> 00:22:11.080
When they told her he is okay,

00:22:11.080 --> 00:22:12.280
she said, I want to see him.

00:22:12.280 --> 00:22:13.580
As soon as she saw him,

00:22:13.580 --> 00:22:14.080
she says,

00:22:14.080 --> 00:22:16.480
كل مصيبة بعده هينا

00:22:16.480 --> 00:22:18.380
All difficulties after this

00:22:18.380 --> 00:22:19.780
they are easy, they are light.

00:22:19.780 --> 00:22:22.080
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us ease.

00:22:22.080 --> 00:22:24.380
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam made dua

00:22:24.380 --> 00:22:26.580
for the families of those

00:22:26.580 --> 00:22:29.880
who were martyred on that particular day

00:22:29.880 --> 00:22:31.080
and Allahu Akbar,

00:22:31.080 --> 00:22:32.480
the Sahaba radi Allahu anhum

00:22:32.480 --> 00:22:33.880
who had remained behind,

00:22:33.880 --> 00:22:36.480
they ensured that they looked after the widows

00:22:36.480 --> 00:22:37.380
and the orphans

00:22:37.380 --> 00:22:38.480
and a lot of these widows

00:22:38.480 --> 00:22:40.580
were married by the Sahaba radi Allahu anhum

00:22:40.580 --> 00:22:42.780
who were left in order to look after them.

00:22:42.780 --> 00:22:45.680
So much so that even the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:22:45.680 --> 00:22:47.780
later on married and we will get to that.

00:22:47.780 --> 00:22:49.380
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:22:49.380 --> 00:22:50.280
an understanding.

00:22:50.280 --> 00:22:51.880
They had to look after these women

00:22:51.880 --> 00:22:53.080
who were left behind.

00:22:53.080 --> 00:22:54.480
They had to look after the children

00:22:54.480 --> 00:22:55.780
who were left behind

00:22:55.780 --> 00:22:57.280
and the best way to do so

00:22:57.280 --> 00:22:59.080
was to marry this widow

00:22:59.080 --> 00:23:01.980
in order for the children to be looked after

00:23:01.980 --> 00:23:04.080
and for the widow to have some male

00:23:04.080 --> 00:23:05.780
who will then look after her

00:23:05.780 --> 00:23:06.980
and be her guardian.

00:23:06.980 --> 00:23:10.780
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us an understanding.

00:23:10.780 --> 00:23:12.780
Now what had happened is

00:23:12.780 --> 00:23:14.680
this was on the seventh day of Shawwal

00:23:14.680 --> 00:23:16.780
according to most of the narrations

00:23:16.780 --> 00:23:19.080
and they had gone back to Madinah Munawwara

00:23:19.080 --> 00:23:20.480
they spent the night there

00:23:20.480 --> 00:23:22.780
and they were waiting

00:23:22.780 --> 00:23:25.380
because the kuffar had left.

00:23:25.380 --> 00:23:27.080
They wanted to enter Madinah

00:23:27.080 --> 00:23:29.680
but Allah had made them go away

00:23:29.680 --> 00:23:30.880
because they were worried

00:23:30.880 --> 00:23:32.080
that if we enter Madinah

00:23:32.080 --> 00:23:34.380
there are so many warriors in Madinah

00:23:34.380 --> 00:23:36.580
who have not taken part in this battle

00:23:36.580 --> 00:23:37.380
they might get up

00:23:37.380 --> 00:23:38.980
and they will attack us once again

00:23:38.980 --> 00:23:40.880
and we might suffer big losses.

00:23:40.880 --> 00:23:42.780
So what happened is

00:23:42.780 --> 00:23:43.980
they had left.

00:23:43.980 --> 00:23:46.580
After they left they got to a certain place

00:23:46.580 --> 00:23:47.580
and they decided

00:23:47.580 --> 00:23:48.980
or they were still deciding

00:23:48.980 --> 00:23:50.480
Abu Sufyan was saying

00:23:50.480 --> 00:23:51.480
let's go back.

00:23:51.480 --> 00:23:52.380
We want to go back

00:23:52.380 --> 00:23:54.880
and we want to attack Madinah.

00:23:54.880 --> 00:23:56.480
And Safwani ibn Umayyah,

00:23:56.480 --> 00:23:58.280
he says no, don't go.

00:23:58.280 --> 00:24:00.080
He was a very intelligent man.

00:24:00.080 --> 00:24:01.780
He says you see at the moment

00:24:01.780 --> 00:24:04.980
we can consider ourselves victorious.

00:24:04.980 --> 00:24:06.980
Why should we go and get a hiding?

00:24:06.980 --> 00:24:08.580
Why should we go back there

00:24:08.580 --> 00:24:10.880
and risk getting

00:24:10.880 --> 00:24:12.880
or suffering loss?

00:24:12.880 --> 00:24:13.580
Subhanallah.

00:24:13.580 --> 00:24:15.780
So he said we're not going to go back.

00:24:15.780 --> 00:24:17.880
However the messenger sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:24:17.880 --> 00:24:20.680
was already instructed by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:24:20.680 --> 00:24:22.380
Seventh of Shawwal they came back.

00:24:22.380 --> 00:24:23.280
They had injuries.

00:24:23.280 --> 00:24:25.980
Some of those injured were still in Madinah and so on.

00:24:25.980 --> 00:24:27.780
He prepared an army the next day

00:24:27.780 --> 00:24:28.980
and he said we need to leave.

00:24:28.980 --> 00:24:29.880
We need to go out

00:24:29.880 --> 00:24:32.280
so that these people don't come into Madinah Munawwarah.

00:24:32.280 --> 00:24:33.580
If they come into Madinah

00:24:33.580 --> 00:24:35.180
we're going to have a problem.

00:24:35.180 --> 00:24:38.080
We're going to have to fight them here on our streets

00:24:38.080 --> 00:24:39.880
meaning in our own suburbs.

00:24:39.880 --> 00:24:40.980
Rather we go out.

00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:43.380
So Hamra al-Asad

00:24:43.380 --> 00:24:46.180
is a place that they got to the following day

00:24:46.180 --> 00:24:47.580
the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:24:47.580 --> 00:24:48.980
on the 8th of Shawwal

00:24:48.980 --> 00:24:51.180
went with only those companions

00:24:51.180 --> 00:24:52.980
who took part in the battle

00:24:52.980 --> 00:24:53.980
besides one or two

00:24:53.980 --> 00:24:55.980
who were granted permission to join them

00:24:55.980 --> 00:24:57.980
and thereafter they went to Hamra al-Asad

00:24:57.980 --> 00:24:59.880
and the mushriks had heard the news

00:24:59.880 --> 00:25:02.580
that these people have camped out there

00:25:02.580 --> 00:25:05.380
and this was also a means of showing them

00:25:05.380 --> 00:25:06.980
that no matter what has happened

00:25:06.980 --> 00:25:08.680
Allahu Akbar.

00:25:08.680 --> 00:25:11.380
We are still ready to defend ourselves.

00:25:11.380 --> 00:25:13.380
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:25:13.380 --> 00:25:18.180
وَلَا تَهِنُوا فِي بْتِغَاءِ الْقَوْمِ

00:25:18.180 --> 00:25:21.480
Don't become slack in pursuit of these people.

00:25:21.480 --> 00:25:23.880
Continue pursuing them.

00:25:23.880 --> 00:25:26.580
إِن تَكُونُوا تَأْلَمُونَ

00:25:26.580 --> 00:25:29.980
فَإِنَّ هُمْ يَأْلَمُونَ كَمَا تَأْلَمُونَ

00:25:29.980 --> 00:25:34.380
وَتَرْجُونَ مِنَ اللَّهِ مَا لَا يَرْجُونَ

00:25:34.380 --> 00:25:35.280
Allah says

00:25:35.280 --> 00:25:37.780
if you are suffering pain and injuries

00:25:37.780 --> 00:25:41.380
you should know that they too are suffering pain and injuries.

00:25:41.380 --> 00:25:43.580
But the difference between you and them

00:25:43.580 --> 00:25:45.480
is you have hope in Allah.

00:25:45.480 --> 00:25:47.080
They don't have hope in anything.

00:25:47.080 --> 00:25:47.980
Allahu Akbar.

00:25:47.980 --> 00:25:49.680
So Allah says go and pursue them.

00:25:49.680 --> 00:25:51.280
And these people went to Hamra al-Assad.

00:25:51.280 --> 00:25:52.580
They spent some time there

00:25:52.580 --> 00:25:57.580
and they came back to Madinatul Munawwarah.

00:25:57.580 --> 00:26:00.180
Another verse that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:26:00.180 --> 00:26:01.780
has made mention of

00:26:01.780 --> 00:26:03.480
which is very important.

00:26:03.480 --> 00:26:06.880
Also teaching the Muslims

00:26:06.880 --> 00:26:10.880
how their morale should be high at all times.

00:26:10.880 --> 00:26:13.380
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:26:13.380 --> 00:26:17.080
Say to them O Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:26:17.080 --> 00:26:23.680
هَلْ تَرَبَّصُونَ بِنَا إِلَّا إِحْدَ الْحُسْنَيَينَ

00:26:23.680 --> 00:26:27.580
Are you waiting for anything to happen with us

00:26:27.580 --> 00:26:30.480
besides the two points of goodness?

00:26:30.480 --> 00:26:32.980
Nothing can happen to us besides goodness.

00:26:32.980 --> 00:26:35.380
We will either be martyred so we will get paradise

00:26:35.380 --> 00:26:36.680
or we will either be victorious

00:26:36.680 --> 00:26:38.280
so we will have victory here.

00:26:38.280 --> 00:26:40.480
So it's either victory here or victory there.

00:26:40.480 --> 00:26:42.280
It's called إِحْدَ الْحُسْنَيَينَ

00:26:42.280 --> 00:26:44.480
One of the two good things can happen to us.

00:26:44.480 --> 00:26:45.980
We can never suffer a loss.

00:26:45.980 --> 00:26:48.480
We are always in a win-win situation.

00:26:48.480 --> 00:26:50.180
This is what the Quran says.

00:26:50.180 --> 00:26:52.480
وَنَحْنُ نَتَرَبَّصُ بِكُمْ

00:26:52.480 --> 00:26:54.580
And as for you, we are waiting.

00:26:54.580 --> 00:26:55.980
We are waiting for what?

00:26:55.980 --> 00:27:02.380
أَنْ يُصِيبَكُمُ اللَّهُ بِعَذَابٍ مِّنْ عِدِهِ أَوْ بِأَيْدِيْنَا

00:27:02.380 --> 00:27:08.380
فَتَرَبَّصُوا إِنَّا مَعَكُمْ مُتَرَبِّصُونَ

00:27:08.480 --> 00:27:11.580
We are waiting for Allah to punish you.

00:27:11.580 --> 00:27:14.880
Either He punishes you on His own

00:27:14.880 --> 00:27:17.180
or He punishes you with our hands.

00:27:17.180 --> 00:27:18.980
Which means if you are victorious,

00:27:18.980 --> 00:27:21.180
Allah will still get hold of you.

00:27:21.180 --> 00:27:22.280
And if we are victorious,

00:27:22.280 --> 00:27:24.280
Allah has punished you with our hands.

00:27:24.280 --> 00:27:25.880
So wait, we are waiting with you.

00:27:25.880 --> 00:27:26.680
Subhanallah.

00:27:26.680 --> 00:27:29.280
So they are in a lose-lose situation

00:27:29.280 --> 00:27:31.680
if we can coin that term quickly.

00:27:31.680 --> 00:27:33.280
And we are in a win-win situation.

00:27:33.280 --> 00:27:33.980
MashaAllah.

00:27:33.980 --> 00:27:35.580
So this was a verse of the Quran

00:27:35.580 --> 00:27:39.280
that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala had revealed,

00:27:39.280 --> 00:27:41.280
boosting the morale of the believers

00:27:41.280 --> 00:27:43.380
and it is an understanding for all of us.

00:27:43.380 --> 00:27:46.180
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:27:46.180 --> 00:27:48.480
The final lesson I want to draw,

00:27:48.480 --> 00:27:49.880
which I've already made mention of,

00:27:49.880 --> 00:27:52.180
but once again we need to say

00:27:52.180 --> 00:27:55.780
that two things that happened on that particular day

00:27:55.780 --> 00:27:57.880
resulted in the suffering of the Muslims.

00:27:57.880 --> 00:27:59.880
One was at tanazwa.

00:27:59.880 --> 00:28:01.480
Tanazwa meaning debate

00:28:01.480 --> 00:28:03.080
and arguing amongst each other.

00:28:03.080 --> 00:28:04.080
Disunity.

00:28:04.080 --> 00:28:05.080
You know, arguing.

00:28:05.080 --> 00:28:05.580
Let's do this.

00:28:05.580 --> 00:28:06.580
No, let's do that.

00:28:06.580 --> 00:28:10.180
Because the Muslims on more than one occasion,

00:28:10.180 --> 00:28:11.780
they were arguing and debating.

00:28:11.780 --> 00:28:12.480
Should we do this?

00:28:12.480 --> 00:28:13.080
Should we do that?

00:28:13.080 --> 00:28:13.880
Shouldn't we do this?

00:28:13.880 --> 00:28:14.780
Perhaps we should do this.

00:28:14.780 --> 00:28:15.680
We should do that.

00:28:15.680 --> 00:28:17.780
That resulted in loss.

00:28:17.780 --> 00:28:20.280
So with us, if we disunite

00:28:20.280 --> 00:28:21.880
and if we disintegrate

00:28:21.880 --> 00:28:24.980
and if we create petty issues between us,

00:28:24.980 --> 00:28:26.880
wallahi we will suffer a loss.

00:28:26.880 --> 00:28:28.080
The Quran says,

00:28:28.080 --> 00:28:33.280
وَالَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا بَعْضُهُمْ أَوْلِيَاءُ بَعْضٍ

00:28:33.280 --> 00:28:36.080
The kuffar are protectors of one another.

00:28:36.080 --> 00:28:37.880
No matter who they are, where they are,

00:28:37.880 --> 00:28:40.480
they will always stand up for one another.

00:28:40.480 --> 00:28:42.280
That's what the Quran says.

00:28:42.280 --> 00:28:44.280
إِلَّا تَفْعَلُوهُ

00:28:44.280 --> 00:28:49.180
تَكُونْ فِتْنَةٌ فِي الْأَرْضِ وَفَسَادٌ كَبِيرٌ

00:28:49.180 --> 00:28:52.880
If you are not going to do exactly the same,

00:28:52.880 --> 00:28:54.880
there is going to be great façade,

00:28:55.880 --> 00:28:58.980
and great fitna on earth.

00:28:58.980 --> 00:29:00.780
What is meant by exactly the same?

00:29:00.780 --> 00:29:03.680
In the same way, the kuffar stand up for one another

00:29:03.680 --> 00:29:05.480
no matter where they are, who they are.

00:29:05.480 --> 00:29:08.580
You as Muslimin need to stand up for one another

00:29:08.580 --> 00:29:10.380
no matter where you are, who you are.

00:29:10.380 --> 00:29:11.980
Solution, subhanallah.

00:29:11.980 --> 00:29:15.080
If we had to adopt just that one ayah today on the globe,

00:29:15.080 --> 00:29:17.980
the problems of the globe would be resolved instantly.

00:29:17.980 --> 00:29:20.380
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us unity

00:29:20.380 --> 00:29:22.580
and may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:29:22.580 --> 00:29:24.080
Part of the plot of shaitan,

00:29:24.080 --> 00:29:26.380
small item, I hate you, I don't talk to you.

00:29:26.380 --> 00:29:27.280
You're not a Muslim.

00:29:27.280 --> 00:29:29.080
You're actually a kafir, astaghfirullah.

00:29:29.080 --> 00:29:31.280
Those are the statements we hear these days.

00:29:31.280 --> 00:29:34.180
People calling other Muslims non-Muslims.

00:29:34.180 --> 00:29:37.180
Why don't we realize that that only serves

00:29:37.180 --> 00:29:38.680
the interests of the enemy?

00:29:38.680 --> 00:29:41.180
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us all

00:29:41.180 --> 00:29:42.680
and grant us ease and goodness.

00:29:42.680 --> 00:29:44.180
So that was a point.

00:29:44.180 --> 00:29:46.480
The second point, we've already spoken about it.

00:29:46.480 --> 00:29:49.780
Never go against the instruction of Allah and His Rasul.

00:29:49.780 --> 00:29:52.680
You cannot achieve happiness through

00:29:52.780 --> 00:29:55.980
the displeasure of the owner of happiness.

00:29:55.980 --> 00:29:57.780
You cannot achieve happiness

00:29:57.780 --> 00:30:00.080
through the displeasure of the owner of happiness.

00:30:00.080 --> 00:30:00.880
You cannot.

00:30:00.880 --> 00:30:03.880
You cannot achieve sustenance or a happy home

00:30:03.880 --> 00:30:05.380
through the owner of sustenance

00:30:05.380 --> 00:30:07.580
and the owner of happiness in your home.

00:30:07.580 --> 00:30:09.980
The only way to get health and happiness

00:30:09.980 --> 00:30:12.180
and contentment and goodness and sustenance

00:30:12.180 --> 00:30:13.880
is through the one who owns it

00:30:13.880 --> 00:30:16.580
by obeying him and by becoming closer to him.

00:30:16.580 --> 00:30:19.880
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:30:19.880 --> 00:30:21.280
In the third year of Hijrah,

00:30:21.380 --> 00:30:24.380
the same year that this battle of Uhud took place,

00:30:24.380 --> 00:30:26.080
the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:30:26.080 --> 00:30:28.180
married the daughter of Umar ibn Al-Khattab

00:30:28.180 --> 00:30:29.080
رضي الله عنه

00:30:29.080 --> 00:30:31.980
who was the widow of Khunais ibn Hudhafa,

00:30:31.980 --> 00:30:33.180
a sahmi.

00:30:33.180 --> 00:30:35.580
And this man had been injured in the battle of Badr.

00:30:35.580 --> 00:30:37.680
According to the most correct narrations,

00:30:37.680 --> 00:30:39.280
he was injured in the battle of Badr

00:30:39.280 --> 00:30:41.180
and later on he passed away.

00:30:41.180 --> 00:30:42.280
And listen to what happened.

00:30:42.280 --> 00:30:45.580
Umar ibn Al-Khattab رضي الله عنه

00:30:45.580 --> 00:30:48.780
he went to Uthman ibn Affan رضي الله عنه.

00:30:48.780 --> 00:30:48.980
He says,

00:30:49.980 --> 00:30:51.580
My daughter Hafsa,

00:30:51.580 --> 00:30:53.980
I want you to marry her.

00:30:53.980 --> 00:30:55.180
Look at this.

00:30:55.180 --> 00:30:57.380
A man coming to his friend and saying,

00:30:57.380 --> 00:30:59.280
I would like you to marry my daughter,

00:30:59.280 --> 00:31:01.180
the widow of Khunais.

00:31:01.180 --> 00:31:03.580
So he looks at Umar ibn Al-Khattab رضي الله عنه

00:31:03.580 --> 00:31:03.880
and he says,

00:31:03.880 --> 00:31:06.880
Look, I have no intention to get married right now.

00:31:06.880 --> 00:31:07.880
Answer.

00:31:07.880 --> 00:31:10.680
Which means he came out of it in a beautiful way.

00:31:10.680 --> 00:31:13.180
And then he went to Abu Bakr Al-Siddiq رضي الله عنه

00:31:13.180 --> 00:31:14.080
Ya Aba Bakr,

00:31:14.080 --> 00:31:16.280
I'd like you to marry my daughter Hafsa,

00:31:16.280 --> 00:31:18.580
the widow of Khunais.

00:31:18.580 --> 00:31:19.580
Abu Bakr was silent,

00:31:19.580 --> 00:31:21.380
no response, no answer.

00:31:21.380 --> 00:31:22.780
And he went away.

00:31:22.780 --> 00:31:24.480
And Umar ibn Al-Khattab رضي الله عنه

00:31:24.480 --> 00:31:25.380
felt that,

00:31:25.380 --> 00:31:27.280
Why didn't I get a reply from this man?

00:31:27.280 --> 00:31:29.080
At least he should have been like Uthman

00:31:29.080 --> 00:31:31.380
and said somehow no, you know.

00:31:31.380 --> 00:31:33.580
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:31:33.580 --> 00:31:36.980
Today people feel bad when someone says no.

00:31:36.980 --> 00:31:37.580
We feel bad,

00:31:37.580 --> 00:31:39.480
so bad that we stop talking to people.

00:31:39.480 --> 00:31:41.280
Wallahi, it's your right, be happy.

00:31:41.280 --> 00:31:43.680
Perhaps your sustenance was not written there.

00:31:43.680 --> 00:31:46.880
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:31:46.880 --> 00:31:49.180
So now, some days later,

00:31:49.180 --> 00:31:50.980
the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:31:50.980 --> 00:31:55.280
proposed to marry the daughter of Umar ibn Al-Khattab رضي الله عنه.

00:31:55.280 --> 00:31:57.880
He was so happy and he agreed immediately.

00:31:57.880 --> 00:31:59.080
The Nikah was done.

00:31:59.080 --> 00:32:01.380
And later on Abu Bakr Al-Siddiq رضي الله عنه

00:32:01.380 --> 00:32:02.880
comes to him and says,

00:32:02.880 --> 00:32:04.780
Oh Umar,

00:32:04.780 --> 00:32:06.080
he says, yes.

00:32:06.080 --> 00:32:08.180
He says, perhaps your heart was hurt

00:32:08.180 --> 00:32:12.280
that I was quiet when you asked me to marry your daughter.

00:32:12.280 --> 00:32:13.480
He says, yes.

00:32:13.480 --> 00:32:16.280
I was expecting some form of reply.

00:32:16.280 --> 00:32:19.280
He says, the only reason why I was silent

00:32:19.280 --> 00:32:21.180
was the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:32:21.180 --> 00:32:22.680
mentioned your daughter

00:32:22.680 --> 00:32:25.580
and I didn't want to release his secret

00:32:25.580 --> 00:32:26.980
to tell you that you know what,

00:32:26.980 --> 00:32:29.180
let the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم marry her.

00:32:29.180 --> 00:32:30.480
So I just remained silent.

00:32:30.480 --> 00:32:32.380
I knew something you didn't know

00:32:32.380 --> 00:32:33.880
and I didn't want to release it,

00:32:33.880 --> 00:32:34.980
so he was silent.

00:32:34.980 --> 00:32:36.980
The clarification, Subhanallah.

00:32:36.980 --> 00:32:38.280
Because the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:32:38.280 --> 00:32:40.980
was concerned about the widows of the Ummah.

00:32:40.980 --> 00:32:42.680
Today, where are the people

00:32:42.680 --> 00:32:45.180
who are concerned about the widows of the Ummah?

00:32:45.180 --> 00:32:46.780
Forget about getting married to them.

00:32:46.780 --> 00:32:47.480
That's one thing,

00:32:47.480 --> 00:32:50.380
but not even rendering assistance to them.

00:32:50.380 --> 00:32:53.380
May Allah سبحانه وتعالى protect us.

00:32:53.380 --> 00:32:55.880
Those were the Sahaba رضي الله عنهم

00:32:55.880 --> 00:32:58.580
and that was Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:32:58.580 --> 00:32:59.780
and the Sahaba,

00:32:59.780 --> 00:33:01.180
look at Umar ibn Al-Khattab.

00:33:01.180 --> 00:33:02.980
What a lesson we learned from him.

00:33:02.980 --> 00:33:05.580
He went out actively telling people,

00:33:05.580 --> 00:33:07.380
look, I want you to marry my daughter.

00:33:07.380 --> 00:33:09.280
How many of us would do that today?

00:33:09.280 --> 00:33:12.180
We have the shackles of culture

00:33:12.180 --> 00:33:14.880
and our daughters and sisters are sitting at home

00:33:14.880 --> 00:33:17.580
because they are cursed by the curse of culture.

00:33:17.580 --> 00:33:18.580
So they are not married

00:33:18.580 --> 00:33:20.580
because it's our fault, not theirs.

00:33:20.580 --> 00:33:21.980
We did not get up, stand up

00:33:21.980 --> 00:33:23.180
and look at the young men

00:33:23.180 --> 00:33:24.880
who come to the Masjid Mashallah.

00:33:24.880 --> 00:33:26.280
Brother, are you married? You're not married.

00:33:26.280 --> 00:33:27.280
Who is your father?

00:33:27.280 --> 00:33:28.580
I'd like to speak to him.

00:33:28.580 --> 00:33:29.680
You know, I've got a daughter.

00:33:29.680 --> 00:33:31.180
Who's going to know you've got a daughter?

00:33:31.180 --> 00:33:32.780
Today, they have a policy.

00:33:32.780 --> 00:33:34.180
Let your daughter be naked

00:33:34.180 --> 00:33:35.880
and go to the mall and everywhere else

00:33:35.880 --> 00:33:37.680
and go to another person's wedding

00:33:37.680 --> 00:33:39.080
when she is half dressed

00:33:39.080 --> 00:33:40.980
so that other people can see her and say,

00:33:40.980 --> 00:33:43.080
wow, she's so beautiful.

00:33:43.080 --> 00:33:44.580
I've got a son.

00:33:45.180 --> 00:33:49.280
The seed that is sown is the seed of haram,

00:33:49.280 --> 00:33:51.180
the seed of shaitan.

00:33:51.180 --> 00:33:52.680
And then we want to get married.

00:33:52.680 --> 00:33:54.680
In five minutes, there is a talaq and a divorce

00:33:54.680 --> 00:33:55.780
and we're back home

00:33:55.780 --> 00:33:57.680
because we did it the wrong way.

00:33:57.680 --> 00:33:58.980
Where are the men?

00:33:58.980 --> 00:34:00.380
Forget about your culture.

00:34:00.380 --> 00:34:01.080
It is wrong.

00:34:01.080 --> 00:34:03.680
It is totally in the bin, subhanallah.

00:34:03.680 --> 00:34:06.480
Wallahi, we suffer because we have left Islam.

00:34:06.480 --> 00:34:07.180
And that's a fact.

00:34:07.180 --> 00:34:08.180
And I'm saying it,

00:34:08.180 --> 00:34:09.680
I have pressed a red button

00:34:09.680 --> 00:34:10.980
because it's a fact.

00:34:10.980 --> 00:34:12.580
There are so many of our sisters

00:34:12.680 --> 00:34:16.380
and daughters who are suffering out there

00:34:16.380 --> 00:34:18.780
and we as men could not even be bothered.

00:34:18.780 --> 00:34:21.580
We have so many people we meet on a daily basis

00:34:21.580 --> 00:34:23.680
who are potential husbands for them

00:34:23.680 --> 00:34:25.580
and we wouldn't talk because why?

00:34:25.580 --> 00:34:27.780
Our culture says a woman must sit at home

00:34:27.780 --> 00:34:29.680
and wait for the ceiling to open up

00:34:29.680 --> 00:34:31.680
and a proposal drops from the top.

00:34:31.680 --> 00:34:32.880
Allah protect us.

00:34:32.880 --> 00:34:33.880
What's that?

00:34:33.880 --> 00:34:35.180
Why can't we throw that away?

00:34:35.180 --> 00:34:35.980
Look at Omar.

00:34:35.980 --> 00:34:37.280
He was better than me and you.

00:34:37.280 --> 00:34:38.780
He is one of those in Jannah

00:34:38.780 --> 00:34:40.080
and he goes to his friends

00:34:40.080 --> 00:34:41.780
and he goes to the others and say,

00:34:41.780 --> 00:34:42.880
Please marry my daughter.

00:34:42.880 --> 00:34:43.880
Would you marry my daughter?

00:34:43.880 --> 00:34:45.280
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:34:45.280 --> 00:34:46.680
grant us a deep understanding.

00:34:46.680 --> 00:34:48.380
As I said, it's a point to learn.

00:34:48.380 --> 00:34:50.380
It's about time we made mention of this.

00:34:50.380 --> 00:34:51.180
There is nothing wrong.

00:34:51.180 --> 00:34:54.580
In Islam, the proposal can come from either side.

00:34:54.580 --> 00:34:56.480
The men or the woman.

00:34:56.480 --> 00:34:57.480
Either side.

00:34:57.480 --> 00:34:59.080
Either can show the interest

00:34:59.080 --> 00:35:00.180
and there is nothing wrong.

00:35:00.180 --> 00:35:00.680
People think,

00:35:00.680 --> 00:35:02.880
No, you see, if we go out,

00:35:02.880 --> 00:35:05.180
then it's like our daughter is inferior.

00:35:05.180 --> 00:35:06.680
Perhaps if they were to come,

00:35:06.680 --> 00:35:07.280
then we can say,

00:35:07.280 --> 00:35:09.680
We gave you our daughter after you asked for it.

00:35:09.680 --> 00:35:11.280
Wallahi, all this is culture.

00:35:11.280 --> 00:35:13.580
That does not bring about happiness or sadness.

00:35:13.580 --> 00:35:15.380
It's got nothing to do with Islam.

00:35:15.380 --> 00:35:16.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:35:16.680 --> 00:35:18.780
grant us an understanding.

00:35:18.780 --> 00:35:19.780
So this was the marriage

00:35:19.780 --> 00:35:21.780
of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:35:21.780 --> 00:35:22.780
Thereafter,

00:35:22.780 --> 00:35:24.480
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:35:24.480 --> 00:35:26.680
married another woman.

00:35:26.680 --> 00:35:29.080
Her name was Zainab binti Khuzaima,

00:35:29.080 --> 00:35:30.980
also a widow.

00:35:30.980 --> 00:35:32.180
And this widow,

00:35:32.180 --> 00:35:33.380
subhanallah,

00:35:33.380 --> 00:35:36.680
she was either the widow of Abdullah ibn Jahsh.

00:35:36.680 --> 00:35:37.780
If that was the case,

00:35:37.780 --> 00:35:38.780
he was killed in Uhud.

00:35:38.780 --> 00:35:40.480
He was martyred in Uhud.

00:35:41.380 --> 00:35:42.580
Or she was,

00:35:42.580 --> 00:35:44.980
according to some of the authentic narrations,

00:35:44.980 --> 00:35:47.780
the widow of Ubaidullah ibn al-Harith,

00:35:47.780 --> 00:35:50.780
who was martyred,

00:35:50.780 --> 00:35:53.580
the first martyr on the day of Badr.

00:35:53.580 --> 00:35:55.380
His name was Ubaidullah ibn al-Harith.

00:35:55.380 --> 00:35:57.280
The more authentic narrations

00:35:57.280 --> 00:35:59.880
point to Ubaidullah ibn al-Harith because

00:35:59.880 --> 00:36:01.380
the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:36:01.380 --> 00:36:04.580
married Zainab binti Khuzaima in Ramadan.

00:36:04.580 --> 00:36:05.680
And if that was the case,

00:36:05.680 --> 00:36:07.880
the Battle of Uhud had not yet taken place.

00:36:07.880 --> 00:36:09.980
So it couldn't have been Abdullah ibn Jahsh,

00:36:09.980 --> 00:36:12.280
because he was only martyred

00:36:12.280 --> 00:36:13.580
during the Battle of Uhud.

00:36:13.580 --> 00:36:15.980
So it was Ubaidullah ibn al-Harith

00:36:15.980 --> 00:36:17.980
and the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:36:17.980 --> 00:36:19.280
proposed for her.

00:36:19.280 --> 00:36:21.480
She was known as Ummul Masakeen.

00:36:21.480 --> 00:36:23.080
And these women were people

00:36:23.080 --> 00:36:25.280
who had served Islam from Mecca.

00:36:25.280 --> 00:36:27.180
And they were people who had served Islam

00:36:27.180 --> 00:36:28.480
in a huge way.

00:36:28.480 --> 00:36:30.480
And they were people who

00:36:30.480 --> 00:36:32.380
had lost their family members.

00:36:32.380 --> 00:36:34.880
They needed someone as their guardian.

00:36:34.880 --> 00:36:36.480
And the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:36:36.480 --> 00:36:38.080
got up and he showed,

00:36:38.080 --> 00:36:39.380
laid the example.

00:36:39.380 --> 00:36:41.580
He proposed for her Ummul Masakeen,

00:36:41.580 --> 00:36:43.380
the mother of the poor.

00:36:43.380 --> 00:36:45.780
She used to go and help the poor at all times.

00:36:45.780 --> 00:36:48.080
And she was a very very generous person,

00:36:48.080 --> 00:36:50.780
even though she did not have much of her own.

00:36:50.780 --> 00:36:52.980
The Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam married her.

00:36:52.980 --> 00:36:55.380
But the marriage only lasted

00:36:55.380 --> 00:36:57.980
eight months because she passed away.

00:36:57.980 --> 00:36:59.680
May Allah be pleased with her.

00:36:59.680 --> 00:37:02.280
So this was the second wife

00:37:02.280 --> 00:37:04.180
of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:37:04.180 --> 00:37:04.880
to pass away.

00:37:04.880 --> 00:37:07.080
The first one was Khadija binti Khuwailid

00:37:07.080 --> 00:37:08.180
radiallahu anha.

00:37:08.180 --> 00:37:10.780
The second one was Zainab binti Khuzaima

00:37:10.780 --> 00:37:11.880
radiallahu anha.

00:37:11.880 --> 00:37:13.780
She was only married eight months

00:37:13.780 --> 00:37:15.380
and thereafter she passed away.

00:37:15.380 --> 00:37:17.280
As we said, she was the widow.

00:37:17.280 --> 00:37:18.780
She was a widow.

00:37:18.780 --> 00:37:20.680
In the same year something very interesting,

00:37:20.680 --> 00:37:22.680
a gift of Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:37:22.680 --> 00:37:25.580
Al-Hasan ibn Ali radiallahu anhu was born

00:37:25.580 --> 00:37:28.680
and this was the grandchild of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:37:28.680 --> 00:37:31.380
most beloved to the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:37:31.380 --> 00:37:35.280
the son of Fatima binti Rasulillahi sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:37:35.280 --> 00:37:37.580
and Ali ibn Abi Talib radiallahu anha.

00:37:37.680 --> 00:37:40.380
Then also the same year,

00:37:40.380 --> 00:37:42.280
the third year of Hijraq,

00:37:42.280 --> 00:37:46.480
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala sent the final verses

00:37:46.480 --> 00:37:49.680
which made alcohol and intoxicants

00:37:49.680 --> 00:37:51.680
completely prohibited.

00:37:51.680 --> 00:37:54.780
Now we pause for a moment.

00:37:54.780 --> 00:37:56.880
The people of Mecca used to drink a lot.

00:37:56.880 --> 00:37:58.380
They used to trade in alcohol.

00:37:58.380 --> 00:37:59.580
Even the people of Medina,

00:37:59.580 --> 00:38:01.980
they used to drink a lot and trade in alcohol.

00:38:01.980 --> 00:38:04.180
When we say drunkards,

00:38:04.180 --> 00:38:05.880
the people used to drink so much

00:38:05.880 --> 00:38:07.180
that they used to fight

00:38:07.180 --> 00:38:08.580
and they used to fight so much

00:38:08.580 --> 00:38:11.580
that it used to result in so many other difficulties

00:38:11.580 --> 00:38:14.380
and problems later on when they were sober.

00:38:14.380 --> 00:38:16.680
So much so that they were drunkards,

00:38:16.680 --> 00:38:20.080
they used to take alcohol and women out to the wars.

00:38:20.080 --> 00:38:22.280
As we saw Battle of Badr, Battle of Uhud,

00:38:22.280 --> 00:38:24.480
these people brought large amounts of alcohol.

00:38:24.480 --> 00:38:26.780
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us.

00:38:26.780 --> 00:38:30.180
So the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was given a verse.

00:38:30.180 --> 00:38:31.680
They asked a question.

00:38:31.680 --> 00:38:33.280
What is the ruling?

00:38:33.280 --> 00:38:36.680
What is the ruling on alcohol and gambling?

00:38:36.680 --> 00:38:38.980
What is the ruling on alcohol and gambling?

00:38:38.980 --> 00:38:39.880
So Allah says,

00:38:39.880 --> 00:38:42.680
يَسْأَلُونَكَ عَنِ الْخَمْرِ وَالْمَيْسِرُ

00:38:42.680 --> 00:38:44.680
O Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:38:44.680 --> 00:38:49.680
they are asking you about alcohol and gambling.

00:38:49.680 --> 00:38:51.380
Why were they asking?

00:38:51.380 --> 00:38:52.480
They were asking

00:38:52.480 --> 00:38:55.980
because people like Abu Bakr knew already

00:38:55.980 --> 00:38:57.680
that this is bad.

00:38:57.680 --> 00:38:59.780
If it wasn't bad, they wouldn't have asked.

00:38:59.780 --> 00:39:01.980
Nobody asks me or asks you,

00:39:01.980 --> 00:39:02.880
can I wear a jacket?

00:39:02.880 --> 00:39:04.980
It's freezing today, subhanallah.

00:39:04.980 --> 00:39:06.780
You'd be wearing the jacket.

00:39:06.780 --> 00:39:07.780
It's not bad,

00:39:07.780 --> 00:39:08.780
but now someone can say,

00:39:08.780 --> 00:39:10.480
no, this is pig skin, can I wear it?

00:39:10.480 --> 00:39:12.180
Because automatically something tells you

00:39:12.180 --> 00:39:13.680
I need to ask a question here.

00:39:13.680 --> 00:39:15.480
There's something wrong with it, perhaps.

00:39:15.480 --> 00:39:16.980
So that's why they knew

00:39:16.980 --> 00:39:18.880
that it causes so much problem.

00:39:18.880 --> 00:39:21.380
Alcohol and gambling causes so much problem.

00:39:21.380 --> 00:39:22.180
They asked.

00:39:22.180 --> 00:39:23.880
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:39:23.880 --> 00:39:25.980
instead of banning it all at once,

00:39:25.980 --> 00:39:27.580
making it difficult sometimes

00:39:27.580 --> 00:39:30.280
for a person who is addicted to it,

00:39:30.280 --> 00:39:31.780
had it happened, it would have happened.

00:39:31.780 --> 00:39:34.380
But Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:39:34.380 --> 00:39:39.480
قُلْ فِيهِ مَا إِثْمٌ كَبِيرٌ وَمَنَافِعُ لِلنَّاسِ

00:39:39.480 --> 00:39:42.780
وَإِثْمُهُ مَا أَكْبَرُ مِنَّفِعِهِ مَا

00:39:42.780 --> 00:39:46.980
Tell them, there is a great sin.

00:39:46.980 --> 00:39:50.080
A great sin in alcohol and gambling.

00:39:50.080 --> 00:39:52.380
But there is also a little bit of benefit.

00:39:52.380 --> 00:39:55.480
But the sin outweighs the benefit.

00:39:55.480 --> 00:39:58.880
And there is much more sin than benefit, harm.

00:39:58.880 --> 00:40:00.480
Much more harm than benefit.

00:40:00.480 --> 00:40:01.380
So from this,

00:40:01.380 --> 00:40:02.980
a lot of the companions understood

00:40:02.980 --> 00:40:05.080
if there is more harm than benefit,

00:40:05.080 --> 00:40:06.180
we need to stay away from it.

00:40:06.180 --> 00:40:07.680
So they started staying away from it.

00:40:07.680 --> 00:40:08.680
Those who were drinking,

00:40:08.680 --> 00:40:10.380
started cutting down and so on.

00:40:10.380 --> 00:40:12.880
People like Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiAllahu anhu,

00:40:12.880 --> 00:40:14.580
the narrations make mention of the fact

00:40:14.580 --> 00:40:17.180
that he never ever drunk, even before Islam.

00:40:17.180 --> 00:40:18.680
He knew that this thing is bad.

00:40:18.680 --> 00:40:20.680
Like Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:40:20.680 --> 00:40:22.680
never went close to it

00:40:22.680 --> 00:40:25.480
by the protection of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:40:25.480 --> 00:40:27.380
So what had happened thereafter

00:40:27.380 --> 00:40:29.480
is after some time,

00:40:29.480 --> 00:40:30.580
people used to drink

00:40:30.580 --> 00:40:32.180
and then when they're in salah,

00:40:32.180 --> 00:40:33.980
they didn't know what they were saying.

00:40:33.980 --> 00:40:35.880
So they would make mistakes.

00:40:35.880 --> 00:40:36.880
Now that is dangerous

00:40:36.880 --> 00:40:38.980
because it's the word of Allah, the Quran.

00:40:38.980 --> 00:40:40.980
So Allah says after some time,

00:40:40.980 --> 00:40:42.380
another verse was revealed.

00:40:42.380 --> 00:40:48.480
Ya ayyuha allatheena amanu la taqrabu s-salata wa antum sukaara

00:40:48.480 --> 00:40:52.180
hatta ta'lamu ma taqoonoon

00:40:52.180 --> 00:40:53.480
O you who believe,

00:40:53.480 --> 00:40:56.580
do not come close to salah and prayer

00:40:56.580 --> 00:40:58.780
in the condition of intoxication

00:40:58.780 --> 00:41:02.180
until you know exactly what you are uttering.

00:41:02.180 --> 00:41:04.380
So as a result, what happened?

00:41:04.380 --> 00:41:06.880
The hours of drinking were cut down.

00:41:06.880 --> 00:41:09.780
So they couldn't drink most of the time.

00:41:09.780 --> 00:41:11.780
They could only drink perhaps after Isha

00:41:11.780 --> 00:41:12.580
for a little while

00:41:12.580 --> 00:41:14.580
because they would have to get up for Fajr

00:41:14.580 --> 00:41:16.680
and perhaps in the morning.

00:41:16.680 --> 00:41:19.480
And in the morning one wonders who would be drinking.

00:41:19.480 --> 00:41:21.880
So in the afternoon they wouldn't be able to drink

00:41:21.880 --> 00:41:23.080
because you have Salatul Asr.

00:41:23.080 --> 00:41:25.780
After Asr, you have Maghrib which is not very far

00:41:25.780 --> 00:41:27.080
and after that you have Isha.

00:41:27.080 --> 00:41:29.080
So the only time was after Isha

00:41:29.080 --> 00:41:31.380
and that too very few people would drink

00:41:31.380 --> 00:41:34.480
until in the third year of Hijra.

00:41:34.480 --> 00:41:36.180
The verse came down.

00:41:36.180 --> 00:41:38.980
Ya ayyuha allatheena amanu

00:41:38.980 --> 00:41:40.280
O you who believe,

00:41:40.280 --> 00:41:43.580
innama al-khamru wa al-maysir wa al-ansab

00:41:43.580 --> 00:41:48.380
wa al-azlamu rijisun min amali shaytaan

00:41:48.380 --> 00:41:52.680
fajtanibuuhu la'alakum tuflihoon

00:41:52.680 --> 00:41:56.580
O you who believe, indeed intoxicants

00:41:56.580 --> 00:42:00.080
as well as gambling, as well as superstition

00:42:00.080 --> 00:42:03.380
and ansab is what they used to do.

00:42:03.380 --> 00:42:06.480
They used to sacrifice some animals in a specific way

00:42:06.480 --> 00:42:08.180
which became prohibited.

00:42:08.180 --> 00:42:12.080
So the superstitions as well as the ansab as lamb

00:42:12.080 --> 00:42:13.480
and alcohol and drinking

00:42:13.480 --> 00:42:16.580
this is abomination from the handiwork of the devil.

00:42:16.580 --> 00:42:20.980
So stay far from it in order that you may succeed.

00:42:20.980 --> 00:42:23.480
That became prohibited.

00:42:23.480 --> 00:42:24.480
It became prohibited.

00:42:24.480 --> 00:42:25.180
Some people say,

00:42:25.180 --> 00:42:27.580
where is the prohibition of alcohol in the Quran?

00:42:27.580 --> 00:42:29.680
If Allah tells you stay far from it,

00:42:29.680 --> 00:42:32.880
it means it is worse than the ordinary sin.

00:42:32.880 --> 00:42:34.880
Just like adultery Allah says,

00:42:34.880 --> 00:42:37.380
wa la taqrabu zina

00:42:37.380 --> 00:42:39.680
don't even go close to it.

00:42:39.680 --> 00:42:41.180
That doesn't mean it's not prohibited.

00:42:41.180 --> 00:42:44.880
It means even to get close to it is prohibited.

00:42:44.880 --> 00:42:48.380
So the same applies here that it is so bad

00:42:48.380 --> 00:42:49.680
stay very far from it.

00:42:49.680 --> 00:42:50.880
Then Allah says,

00:42:50.880 --> 00:42:56.080
Innama yuridu ash-shaytanu an yuqi'a baynakumu al-adawata

00:42:56.080 --> 00:42:59.980
wa al-baghda'a fi al-khamri wa al-mainsir

00:42:59.980 --> 00:43:01.280
Indeed,

00:43:01.280 --> 00:43:05.180
shaytan wants to create enmity and hatred

00:43:05.180 --> 00:43:09.380
between you in alcohol and gambling.

00:43:09.380 --> 00:43:11.180
Through alcohol and gambling,

00:43:11.180 --> 00:43:12.880
there is enmity, there is hatred,

00:43:12.880 --> 00:43:14.780
there is problem, there is war.

00:43:14.780 --> 00:43:16.780
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says,

00:43:16.780 --> 00:43:19.880
fa hal antum muntahoon

00:43:19.880 --> 00:43:21.680
The verse continues that

00:43:21.680 --> 00:43:26.080
shaytan intends to distract you from Salah

00:43:26.080 --> 00:43:28.380
and the remembrance of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:43:28.380 --> 00:43:30.280
So are you going to leave it?

00:43:30.280 --> 00:43:31.380
It's a question.

00:43:31.380 --> 00:43:33.280
When this verse was revealed,

00:43:33.280 --> 00:43:36.080
the Prophet salallahu alaihi wa sallam had read it.

00:43:36.080 --> 00:43:38.480
The caller went out calling people,

00:43:38.480 --> 00:43:41.180
ala innal khamra qad hurrim

00:43:41.180 --> 00:43:43.180
He called out,

00:43:43.180 --> 00:43:46.280
behold alcohol has been made prohibited.

00:43:46.280 --> 00:43:48.780
Alcohol has been made prohibited.

00:43:48.780 --> 00:43:52.080
It is reported that the gullies of Medina

00:43:52.080 --> 00:43:55.980
were flowing with alcohol which people threw out

00:43:55.980 --> 00:43:58.680
as a result of listening to a caller

00:43:58.680 --> 00:44:01.780
calling the instruction of Allah

00:44:01.780 --> 00:44:04.580
that alcohol is prohibited.

00:44:04.580 --> 00:44:05.480
Subhanallah.

00:44:05.480 --> 00:44:08.780
Look at how those who had it in their mouths spat it out.

00:44:08.780 --> 00:44:11.380
Those who had it in their containers spat it out.

00:44:11.380 --> 00:44:13.980
Whatever or should I say poured it out.

00:44:13.980 --> 00:44:15.980
Whatever they had had, they poured it out.

00:44:15.980 --> 00:44:17.780
Look at how they did not look at

00:44:17.780 --> 00:44:19.380
how much I'm going to lose.

00:44:19.380 --> 00:44:20.080
What might happen?

00:44:20.080 --> 00:44:21.780
Hey, there's 200 liters here.

00:44:21.780 --> 00:44:23.980
Perhaps I could sell it to those people of the book

00:44:23.980 --> 00:44:26.480
and perhaps this, nothing of that nature.

00:44:26.480 --> 00:44:27.780
Throw it out immediately.

00:44:27.780 --> 00:44:31.480
These were Sahaba of Rasulullah salallahu alaihi wa sallam.

00:44:31.480 --> 00:44:34.480
This was the prohibition of alcohol

00:44:34.480 --> 00:44:36.880
as well as gambling.

00:44:36.880 --> 00:44:40.280
Now one might ask when the Quran says

00:44:40.280 --> 00:44:42.380
that gambling and alcohol,

00:44:42.380 --> 00:44:46.180
there is some goodness and mostly harm.

00:44:46.180 --> 00:44:47.680
Why was that said?

00:44:47.680 --> 00:44:48.780
It's a good question.

00:44:48.780 --> 00:44:50.280
So if you open the books of tafsir,

00:44:50.280 --> 00:44:52.180
you find a point.

00:44:52.180 --> 00:44:54.980
At the time what the Bedouin Arabs used to do,

00:44:54.980 --> 00:44:56.180
whenever they gambled,

00:44:56.180 --> 00:44:57.280
they knew that this is wrong

00:44:57.280 --> 00:44:59.980
because 500 people are putting

00:44:59.980 --> 00:45:01.980
perhaps a gold coin each

00:45:01.980 --> 00:45:03.480
and one man goes away with everything,

00:45:03.480 --> 00:45:04.580
the rest of them lost.

00:45:04.580 --> 00:45:07.080
So actually more people lose than gain.

00:45:07.080 --> 00:45:09.680
And the one who gains for your interest

00:45:09.680 --> 00:45:10.680
and I have done a study,

00:45:10.680 --> 00:45:12.580
it's not so difficult these days

00:45:12.580 --> 00:45:15.280
with Sheikh Google so near.

00:45:15.280 --> 00:45:17.980
If you look at all those who have won

00:45:17.980 --> 00:45:20.580
huge lotteries on the globe,

00:45:20.580 --> 00:45:22.280
their families have been destroyed

00:45:22.280 --> 00:45:23.780
within a short space of time

00:45:23.780 --> 00:45:26.280
and a lot of them have died drunkards

00:45:26.280 --> 00:45:28.680
and people who have really suffered

00:45:28.680 --> 00:45:30.480
because that is cursed money.

00:45:30.480 --> 00:45:32.280
It is cursed to the degree,

00:45:32.280 --> 00:45:33.680
it's not from your sweat,

00:45:33.680 --> 00:45:34.780
you are taking risks,

00:45:34.780 --> 00:45:36.980
you are eating other people's monies

00:45:36.980 --> 00:45:40.180
and if those who take part in these lottoes

00:45:40.180 --> 00:45:41.480
on a monthly basis

00:45:41.480 --> 00:45:43.780
have to save that money for two or three years,

00:45:43.780 --> 00:45:46.080
it becomes as big as one of the prizes.

00:45:46.080 --> 00:45:47.980
Anyway, may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:45:47.980 --> 00:45:49.980
grant us a deep understanding

00:45:49.980 --> 00:45:51.080
and may He open our doors.

00:45:51.080 --> 00:45:52.880
What they used to do at the time,

00:45:52.880 --> 00:45:54.080
as soon as they win,

00:45:54.080 --> 00:45:56.980
they give out the amount to charity.

00:45:56.980 --> 00:45:59.280
They used to give out the amount to the poor,

00:45:59.280 --> 00:46:00.480
to the charity

00:46:00.480 --> 00:46:03.680
and this is why some of the scholars say

00:46:03.680 --> 00:46:05.280
that this was the little goodness

00:46:05.280 --> 00:46:07.980
that they used to talk about up to today.

00:46:07.980 --> 00:46:08.980
There are people who tell you,

00:46:08.980 --> 00:46:10.380
let me take part in the lottery,

00:46:10.380 --> 00:46:13.480
if I win, I will go and give it to a charity.

00:46:13.480 --> 00:46:15.180
Why should we say this?

00:46:15.180 --> 00:46:16.480
And why should we even do it?

00:46:16.480 --> 00:46:18.680
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:46:18.680 --> 00:46:20.180
You really want to give a charity?

00:46:20.180 --> 00:46:21.680
Give your own wealth.

00:46:21.680 --> 00:46:23.880
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala open our doors.

00:46:23.880 --> 00:46:25.180
Something else that had happened

00:46:25.180 --> 00:46:26.780
also in the third year of Hijrah,

00:46:26.780 --> 00:46:27.880
very important.

00:46:27.880 --> 00:46:29.980
The rules of inheritance were laid down

00:46:29.980 --> 00:46:31.380
for your information.

00:46:31.380 --> 00:46:32.580
At that particular time,

00:46:32.580 --> 00:46:34.880
just before this,

00:46:34.880 --> 00:46:36.280
women were inherited.

00:46:36.280 --> 00:46:38.480
Someone dies, they would inherit the wife.

00:46:38.480 --> 00:46:39.780
Someone else, for example,

00:46:39.780 --> 00:46:40.680
owed someone money,

00:46:40.680 --> 00:46:41.980
the daughter would be paid.

00:46:41.980 --> 00:46:43.280
Someone else, for example,

00:46:43.280 --> 00:46:44.680
had a problem with someone

00:46:44.680 --> 00:46:45.980
and they would give their sister

00:46:45.980 --> 00:46:47.380
or their daughter and so on.

00:46:47.380 --> 00:46:49.080
When they died, this is what would happen.

00:46:49.080 --> 00:46:51.980
And these women were treated like commodities.

00:46:51.980 --> 00:46:55.080
And they were never ever spoken about

00:46:55.080 --> 00:46:57.580
in terms of the wealth that the men had had.

00:46:57.580 --> 00:47:00.980
They weren't even allowed to own anything of value.

00:47:00.980 --> 00:47:02.780
It was to be used for the men.

00:47:02.780 --> 00:47:03.580
That's it.

00:47:03.580 --> 00:47:04.580
When Islam came,

00:47:04.580 --> 00:47:06.980
it allowed individual ownership.

00:47:06.980 --> 00:47:09.280
A woman can own and that is her property.

00:47:09.280 --> 00:47:09.880
That's it.

00:47:09.880 --> 00:47:11.180
Subhanallah.

00:47:11.180 --> 00:47:12.980
No one has a say in it.

00:47:12.980 --> 00:47:14.580
Besides herself, obviously,

00:47:14.580 --> 00:47:16.780
she can be guided if she's doing something wrong.

00:47:16.780 --> 00:47:18.880
But if she would like, that's her money,

00:47:18.880 --> 00:47:20.580
nobody can usurp it from her.

00:47:20.580 --> 00:47:22.180
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:47:22.180 --> 00:47:24.280
grant our women protection as well.

00:47:24.280 --> 00:47:26.980
Sometimes from our own evil.

00:47:26.980 --> 00:47:29.180
Sometimes we are the culprits

00:47:29.180 --> 00:47:32.680
and we are the ones who oppress our own women.

00:47:32.680 --> 00:47:35.280
So at this stage,

00:47:35.280 --> 00:47:38.480
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala revealed verses

00:47:38.480 --> 00:47:42.180
declaring that eight categories of women

00:47:42.180 --> 00:47:43.580
shall inherit wealth

00:47:43.580 --> 00:47:45.580
and only four categories of men

00:47:45.580 --> 00:47:47.180
shall inherit wealth.

00:47:47.180 --> 00:47:49.780
So if you look at the number of categories of men

00:47:49.780 --> 00:47:52.480
who inherit, four of them.

00:47:52.480 --> 00:47:54.480
And if you look at the number of categories of women

00:47:54.480 --> 00:47:56.080
who inherit, eight categories.

00:47:56.080 --> 00:47:57.080
And on top of that,

00:47:57.080 --> 00:47:59.480
the largest shares to be given

00:47:59.480 --> 00:48:00.980
are to be given to women.

00:48:00.980 --> 00:48:02.980
So you have a thuluthan,

00:48:02.980 --> 00:48:04.880
which means two-thirds.

00:48:04.880 --> 00:48:06.280
Two-thirds is given to whom?

00:48:06.280 --> 00:48:08.080
Open the books which explain inheritance.

00:48:08.080 --> 00:48:09.180
Open the Quran

00:48:09.180 --> 00:48:10.080
and you will find

00:48:10.180 --> 00:48:12.480
two-thirds is only used

00:48:12.480 --> 00:48:15.280
where women are in the picture.

00:48:15.280 --> 00:48:15.980
Subhanallah.

00:48:15.980 --> 00:48:17.980
It's never used for men.

00:48:17.980 --> 00:48:18.880
Another one,

00:48:18.880 --> 00:48:22.580
50% of all wealth the husband gets

00:48:22.580 --> 00:48:25.780
if the wife has left behind no children.

00:48:25.780 --> 00:48:28.380
But in the case of a single daughter,

00:48:28.380 --> 00:48:31.580
she collects 50% of what her father has left

00:48:31.580 --> 00:48:33.080
or her mother has left.

00:48:33.080 --> 00:48:34.380
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:48:34.380 --> 00:48:35.780
grant us a deep understanding.

00:48:35.780 --> 00:48:39.380
Now one might ask these laws of inheritance.

00:48:39.380 --> 00:48:43.580
How were they laid down?

00:48:43.580 --> 00:48:45.080
If we look at how they were laid down,

00:48:45.080 --> 00:48:46.280
Allah says,

00:48:46.280 --> 00:48:48.680
you O man have no choice

00:48:48.680 --> 00:48:50.380
regarding how your wealth

00:48:50.380 --> 00:48:52.680
shall be divided after you die.

00:48:52.680 --> 00:48:53.680
You have no choice.

00:48:53.680 --> 00:48:54.780
The wealth is ours.

00:48:54.780 --> 00:48:55.980
It belonged to us.

00:48:55.980 --> 00:48:57.480
We lent it to you for a while.

00:48:57.480 --> 00:48:58.380
Once you die,

00:48:58.380 --> 00:49:00.880
we will decide how it will be distributed.

00:49:00.880 --> 00:49:02.380
That is the law of the Quran.

00:49:02.380 --> 00:49:04.580
The only thing Allah has given me and you,

00:49:04.580 --> 00:49:06.780
Allah says up to 33%,

00:49:06.780 --> 00:49:10.280
you can give anyone whom we have not given.

00:49:10.280 --> 00:49:11.780
So if Allah has given someone,

00:49:11.780 --> 00:49:13.480
you cannot increase or decrease.

00:49:13.480 --> 00:49:14.280
Never.

00:49:14.280 --> 00:49:16.580
And if Allah has not given someone

00:49:16.580 --> 00:49:18.280
from 33%,

00:49:18.280 --> 00:49:20.580
you can actually write down a will to say,

00:49:20.580 --> 00:49:22.480
I'd like to give this person so much.

00:49:22.480 --> 00:49:23.480
The rest of it,

00:49:23.480 --> 00:49:24.880
it's Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:49:24.880 --> 00:49:25.680
He decides.

00:49:25.680 --> 00:49:28.280
So whether you've got along with your son or not,

00:49:28.280 --> 00:49:30.680
or whether your daughter listened to you or not,

00:49:30.680 --> 00:49:33.680
they will definitely get from Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:49:33.680 --> 00:49:34.580
that's a share.

00:49:34.580 --> 00:49:36.680
Unless they have engaged in a deed

00:49:36.680 --> 00:49:39.380
which prohibits them from the share,

00:49:39.380 --> 00:49:40.580
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:49:40.580 --> 00:49:42.580
safeguard us such as murder and so on,

00:49:42.580 --> 00:49:43.880
in that particular case,

00:49:43.880 --> 00:49:45.580
they will be blocked from receiving.

00:49:45.580 --> 00:49:47.380
So this is why we need to know,

00:49:47.380 --> 00:49:47.880
all of us,

00:49:47.880 --> 00:49:50.180
and many Muslims don't know this for some reason,

00:49:50.180 --> 00:49:51.280
it's in the Quran,

00:49:51.280 --> 00:49:52.680
very loud and clear,

00:49:52.680 --> 00:49:55.580
that Allah has decreed these as shares.

00:49:55.580 --> 00:49:57.780
Now there is one other point we need to speak about,

00:49:57.780 --> 00:49:58.480
and that is,

00:49:58.480 --> 00:50:03.780
why is it that it seems that women get half of that of a male?

00:50:03.780 --> 00:50:04.480
The answer is,

00:50:05.080 --> 00:50:07.380
women actually get more than a male.

00:50:07.380 --> 00:50:09.180
The male is a guardian.

00:50:09.180 --> 00:50:12.980
He is supposed to look after the closest females to him.

00:50:12.980 --> 00:50:17.180
And every female is to be looked after in Islam,

00:50:17.180 --> 00:50:19.680
in terms of food, clothing and accommodation,

00:50:19.680 --> 00:50:21.780
by her closest male relative,

00:50:21.780 --> 00:50:22.880
either the husband,

00:50:22.880 --> 00:50:24.380
or the adult son,

00:50:24.380 --> 00:50:25.780
or the father,

00:50:25.780 --> 00:50:27.180
or the brothers,

00:50:27.180 --> 00:50:29.380
or the uncles.

00:50:29.380 --> 00:50:34.080
If a woman has you as her closest male relative,

00:50:34.080 --> 00:50:38.180
you are sinful if you don't provide her with food, clothing and accommodation.

00:50:38.180 --> 00:50:39.180
Subhanallah.

00:50:39.180 --> 00:50:40.280
That is Islam.

00:50:40.280 --> 00:50:44.380
So women must be taken care of by their closest male relatives.

00:50:44.380 --> 00:50:45.180
That's the law.

00:50:45.180 --> 00:50:47.380
So why then do they need any wealth?

00:50:47.380 --> 00:50:48.980
The truth is they don't.

00:50:48.980 --> 00:50:49.880
They don't need it.

00:50:49.880 --> 00:50:51.380
Allah gave them as a token,

00:50:51.380 --> 00:50:53.980
just in case me and you don't look after them.

00:50:53.980 --> 00:50:55.380
Subhanallah.

00:50:55.380 --> 00:50:56.180
Amazing.

00:50:56.180 --> 00:51:00.180
So when a man gets out of $75,000,

00:51:00.180 --> 00:51:02.080
if a man gets $50,000,

00:51:02.080 --> 00:51:04.680
and his sister gets $25,000,

00:51:04.680 --> 00:51:06.080
from the $50,000,

00:51:06.080 --> 00:51:08.780
that man has to look after his wife, his children,

00:51:08.780 --> 00:51:09.980
and his family members,

00:51:09.980 --> 00:51:12.780
as well as his own sister from the $50,000.

00:51:12.780 --> 00:51:15.180
So it's divided into approximately eight people.

00:51:15.180 --> 00:51:17.680
And the $25,000 she got, it's hers.

00:51:17.680 --> 00:51:19.280
To save, to be happy.

00:51:19.280 --> 00:51:21.180
To go, masha'Allah, now and again somewhere,

00:51:21.180 --> 00:51:23.180
and to be able to spend a little bit of money.

00:51:23.180 --> 00:51:26.080
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant our women an understanding.

00:51:26.080 --> 00:51:28.180
Wallahi, Islam has honored them,

00:51:28.180 --> 00:51:30.180
and raised them far above

00:51:30.180 --> 00:51:32.680
any other religion could have ever raised them.

00:51:32.680 --> 00:51:34.480
And Allah has given them dignity,

00:51:34.480 --> 00:51:36.180
and Allah has given them a position.

00:51:36.180 --> 00:51:38.480
The difficulty is sometimes we as men

00:51:38.480 --> 00:51:40.080
do not even know the position

00:51:40.080 --> 00:51:41.480
that is granted to our women.

00:51:41.480 --> 00:51:44.380
And sometimes not only do we not look after them,

00:51:44.380 --> 00:51:47.580
but we cheat them out of their share of inheritance.

00:51:47.580 --> 00:51:50.080
We don't even speak about it years pass,

00:51:50.080 --> 00:51:51.780
and we don't even give them their share.

00:51:51.780 --> 00:51:54.180
And yet sometimes we are sitting with everything.

00:51:54.180 --> 00:51:56.180
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala safeguard us,

00:51:56.180 --> 00:51:57.780
and grant us ease and goodness.

00:51:57.780 --> 00:51:58.880
Insha'Allah, tomorrow,

00:51:58.880 --> 00:52:01.380
we will look at more of what was revealed

00:52:01.380 --> 00:52:02.680
in that particular year,

00:52:02.680 --> 00:52:04.980
and we will go into the following year,

00:52:04.980 --> 00:52:07.480
when there were several other skirmishes that took place.

00:52:07.480 --> 00:52:09.580
And we ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:52:09.580 --> 00:52:11.380
to grant us protection in the same way

00:52:11.380 --> 00:52:13.680
that He protected Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:52:13.680 --> 00:52:14.680
and his companions.

00:52:14.680 --> 00:52:16.280
And we ask Allah to grant us Jannah

00:52:16.280 --> 00:52:17.280
until we meet again.

00:52:17.280 --> 00:52:19.580
Wa salallahu wa sallam wa baraka ala Nabina Muhammad

00:52:19.580 --> 00:52:20.580
Subhanallah wa bi hamdihi,

00:52:20.580 --> 00:52:21.980
Subhanaka Allahumma wa bi hamdiki

00:52:21.980 --> 00:52:23.280
Ash hadu an la ilaha illa anta

00:52:23.280 --> 00:52:24.480
Nastaghfiruka wa natubuhi

00:52:24.480 --> 00:52:28.280
Alhamdu Billahi Rabbil alamin

00:52:28.280 --> 00:52:30.880
Ar Rahman Ar Raheem

00:52:30.880 --> 00:52:33.880
Maliki Yawm al Deen

00:52:33.880 --> 00:52:35.480
Iyyaka na'budu
